episodesByNumber.tease: For this New  Sounds, hear music based on themes of tears and melancholy, including John Dowland's hit song, and trombone music from Austria.

episodesByNumber.title: #3477: Music With Folk Roots
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to ensemble pieces which draw from folk music the world over on this New Sounds program, like the Tajik band with an Israeli musician, or Norwegian folk fiddling and laptops.

episodesByNumber.title: #3478: Funeral Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear musical moods not usually associated with funerals, from West African funeral drumming to a jazz march from Norwegian musician Stian Carstensen on this New Sounds.

episodesByNumber.title: #3479: Dependable Groove Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Whether it's piano-driven, horn-driven, or interlocking rhythms of guitar music, listen to music with a steady groove on this edition of New Sounds, like the Blue Cranes and Kaki King.

episodesByNumber.title: #3480: With Yungchen Lhamo & Anton Batagov
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, Tibetan devotional singer Yungchen Lhamo and Russian pianist/composer Anton Batagov discuss their recent musical collaboration - "Tayatha."

episodesByNumber.title: #3481: Latin American Poetry Settings
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to contemporary settings of great Latin-American poets on this New Sounds, including the poetry of Chilean poet Elias Letelier by Canadian composer/electric guitarist Tim Brady.

episodesByNumber.title: #3482: New Music a la Turk (or From Turkey)
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear Turkish music on this New Sounds, with traditional Turkish rhythms, melodies,  &  instruments. Plus, listen to Turkish musicians, collaborating with the Canadian group, Esmerine.

episodesByNumber.title: #3484: Variations on Themes by Brian Eno
episodesByNumber.tease: On this New Sounds, listen to distinctive takes on the music of Brian Eno, including "Paraphrase on Themes of Brian Eno" by Timo Andres and Conrad Tao's work for piano and iPad.

episodesByNumber.title: #3485: Music with Multiple Hyphens
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to blends of world music, minimalism, chamber music, jazz, rock and post-rock, big band, Ethio-jazz, folk music from the world over, Celtic, Latin jazz for this New Sounds.

episodesByNumber.title: #3486: Unremembered, by Sarah Kirkland Snider
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear the world premiere of Sarah Kirkland Snider's song-cycle for 7 vocalists  &  chamber orchestra,"Unremembered," setting poetry by /writer Nathaniel Bellows, from New Sounds Live 2013.

episodesByNumber.title: #3487: Recent Guitar-Centric Recordings
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear new guitar-centric music on this New Sounds program including music by John Zorn, as played by Pat Metheny, a tune from the South African guitarist Guy Buttery, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3488: Songs for Peace, From Mali
episodesByNumber.tease: On this edition of New Sounds, hear politically-inspired music from Mali, including music from Vieux Farka Touré's album "Mon Pays," the collective 'Voices United for Mali',  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3489: Not Quite Art Songs
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to some not-quite art songs on this New Sounds program, including new music from the Swedish singer, keyboardist and songwriter Anna von Hausswolff, June Tabor, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3490: New Music With Accordion
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear new music from accordionist, keyboard player, and composer Ted Reichman, focusing on connections between improvisation and various forms of folk, popular music, and jazz.

episodesByNumber.title: #3491: Electronic-Based Works
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to a bevy of electronic-based works for this New Sounds program, including music from Oneohtrix Point Never, Jon Hopkins, Laurie Spiegel, and Frances White.

episodesByNumber.title: #3492: 40 Years (and more) of Kronos Quartet
episodesByNumber.tease: Founding violinist of Kronos Quartet, David Harrington joins John Schaefer to take a retrospective look at 40-plus years of musical adventure.

episodesByNumber.title: #3493: New Sounds of Black Sabbath
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear an hour of Black Sabbath arrangements on tonight's New Sounds show, including "Iron Man" done up as folktronica, heavy-jazz, and a Columbian cumbia take. And more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3495: New Blues
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear new blues on tonight's New Sounds, including music from the likes of Bobby McFerrin and the recent record "Spirityouall."

episodesByNumber.title: #3496:  El Camino - a Musical Pilgrimage
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, listen to music inspired by El Camino, the ancient pilgrimage route to Santiago de Compostela in Spain, thought to be the final resting place of the Saint James.

episodesByNumber.title: #3497: Fair Play for Women
episodesByNumber.tease: This New Sounds program goes for works by women, including music from Julianna Barwick's recent, "Nepenthe," Canadian percussionist Beverley Johnston,  &  a song cycle by Leah Kardos.

episodesByNumber.title: #3498: Gated Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music made using noise gates on this New Sounds program, including works by Joshua Fried and his musical shoes, and Daniel Figgis.

episodesByNumber.title: #3499: Hot Brass Band Party
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to as much brass band music as we can handle on this New Sounds program.  From Egypt to Rajastan, from New Orleans to Benin, there's party music aplenty.

episodesByNumber.title: #3500: Pianist Composers
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music by pianist/composers on this New Sounds, including works from the Berlin-based pianist/piano-builder Davide Martello, Italian pianist/composer Ludovico Einaudi  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3501: Post-Rock & Soundtracks
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to some post-rock music on this New Sounds program, featuring a soundtrack to "Prince Avalanche" by Explosions in the Sky, along with music by Clint Mansell, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3502: Still More World Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Sample an hour of global music rooted in traditional instruments, and western ones, featuring music by Syrian dabke artist Omar Souleyman and music from Ethio-jazzer Mulatu Astatke .

episodesByNumber.title: #3503: Inspired by Sci-Fi
episodesByNumber.tease: It's nerd-night! There's music inspired by Sci-Fi books  &  film for this New Sounds program. Listen to the internet opera/sonic book by Mendi  &  Keith Obadike, "The Sour Thunder,"  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3504: New Music From Southern Italy
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear song and dances in the music of Southern Italy on this New Sounds, with music from Enzo Avitabile  &  Bottari, percussionist Alessandra Belloni, and Ludovico Einaudi.

episodesByNumber.title: #3505: World Music Ports of Call
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to an hour of world music which takes us to Madagascar, to Poland, and the Reunion Islands in the Indian Ocean, and to various other ports of call.

episodesByNumber.title: #3506:  New Music From the Concert Hall
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to some new music from the concert hall from composer, singer, violinist and multi-instrumentalist Caleb Burhans and his latest release, the "emo-classical" epic, "Evensong."

episodesByNumber.title: #3507: Mid-Sized Ensembles
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music from mid-sized ensembles on this New Sounds. There's music from Daniel Wohl and TRANSIT from his record, "Corps Exquis," as a sextet, involving electronics,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3508: New Soundtracks
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to an hour of recent soundtracks for both film and dance, featuring music from Philip Glass, Icelandic composer Jóhann Jóhannsson, and cellist Lori Goldston.

episodesByNumber.title: #3509: With John Zorn
episodesByNumber.tease: Composer, producer, performer, conductor, record label founder, and MacArthur Genius John Zorn joins us to present selections from his massive Masada Project, Book 2: Book of Angels.

episodesByNumber.title: #3510: Near East/South Asian Connections
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, listen to music that mixes together the traditions of South Asia and the middle East and just as far west as Turkey. Listen to Nashaz, Kayhan Kalhor, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3511: New Music, Old Roots
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to new music with old roots, including music by New York band Barbez, U.K. based quartet Sons of Kemet, klezmer-based music from clarinetist David Krakauer, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3512:  Classical-Adjacent Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear songs and instrumental pieces that are informed by classical music, yet ones which expertly ride the divide between classical and post-rock, or perhaps classical and electronica.

episodesByNumber.title: #3513: With Guy Buttery
episodesByNumber.tease: South African fingerstyle guitarist Guy Buttery performs in our studio without effects. Listen as he plays guitar like a zither, as an extension of tapping, to achieve slap harmonics.

episodesByNumber.title: #3514: The Non-Western Orchestra
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music that features the orchestra as a non-western ensemble, including Bombay Dub Orchestra, Master Musicians of Jajouka,  &  Jherek Bischoff arranging the Congotronics project.

episodesByNumber.title: #3515: Music for Voices and Strings
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, listen to new music from violinist/vocalist Caleb Burhans off his latest release "Evensong," plus music by Nico Muhly, ambient-ish music by Gyorgy Ligeti and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3517: New Music from Mali
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music from Mali, mostly recordings from 2012, featuring Rokia Traoré, Sidi Touré, Amadou  &  Mariam with members of TV on the Radio, the group Tamikrest, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3518: The Sounds of Sunda
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music from Sunda (the western portion of Java), in Indonesia.  &  from western bands like Tribecastan, the Evergreen Club Contemporary Gamelan of Canada, Lou Harrison, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3519: New Music/Baroque Forms
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear new music based on baroque forms like passacaglias, bourrees and courantes on this New Sounds, featuring excerpts from Caroline Shaw's "Partita for 8 Voices" by Roomful of Teeth.

episodesByNumber.title: #3520: Desert Songs
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music made in deserts the world over on this New Sounds, like the overtone singing-meets-country music Uyghur group Qetiq, and music from the Indian desert state of Rajasthan.

episodesByNumber.title: #3521: All Acoustic
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear all-acoustic music, including works from Colin Jacobsen  &  the Silk Road Ensemble, violinist Hilary Hahn, and percussive baritone uke creations by guitarist Kevin Hufnagel.

episodesByNumber.title: #3522: Works for Multiple Electric Guitars
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music for multiple electric guitars, from guitarists Dustin Wong, Dominic Frasca and Pat Metheny playing Steve Reich's Electric Counterpoint.

episodesByNumber.title: #3523: Electroacoustic Music, Old and New
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear electroacoustic music, old  &  new, with minimalist dream-pop from Montreal-based outfit Saltland, Austin-hatched drone duo Stars of the Lid, German band Popul Vuh  &  Tim Hecker.

episodesByNumber.title: #3524: "String" Trios
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to mostly unconventional string trios involving Malagasy zither, South Indian violin, West African kora, Chinese erhu, guitars of all sorts, banjo and much more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3525: New Sounds Live: Music of Caroline Shaw
episodesByNumber.tease: From the New Sounds Live Concert Series, listen to music by Pulitzer Prize-winning composer Caroline Shaw, including the vocal acrobatics of the octet Roomful of Teeth. And more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3526: Hybrid Ensembles
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear new music from Uri Sharlin  &  the DogCat Ensemble - a trio that infuses Israel and Brazil into New York. Plus, music from the Montreal-based chamber jazzers Esmerine,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3527: Global Jazz
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear global jazz like Vijay Iyer's "Playlist For An Extreme Occasion" - an intricate suite for piano, gaita, percussion, tabla, sheng, violin, viola  &  cello for the Silk Road Ensemble.

episodesByNumber.title: #3528: New Sounds Live: Music of Caroline Shaw, Part 2
episodesByNumber.tease: From a 2013 New Sounds Live at the Winter Garden at Brookfield Place, listen to more music by Pulitzer Prize-winning composer Caroline Shaw.

episodesByNumber.title: #3530: Music for Strings, Old and New
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to Bryce Dessner's string quartet "Little Blue Something" with the piece that inspired it: "Little Blue Nothing" by Czech duo Irena Havlova  &  Vojtěch Havel,  &  other string music.

episodesByNumber.title: #3531: Music Inspired by Architecture
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music inspired by architecture, like Neil Rolnick's electronic violin concerto, "Gardening at Gropius House" featuring violinist Todd Reynolds,  &  members of Alarm Will Sound.

episodesByNumber.title: #3532: New Music for Piano
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear piano music from Canadian pianist/composer Heather Schmidt, as well as Canadian composer Ann Southam. Plus, some of Anton Batagov's alleged Letters of Sergei Rachmaninoff  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3533: Sir John Tavener, a New Sounds Tribute
#3534: World Music Roots
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music built around recordings of world music, including a work by Evan Ziporyn, built around Balinese vocalist Ni Lemon's recording, "Wagarasi,"  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3535: Unexpected World Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music from Yo Yo Ma's Silk Road Ensemble, in a 4-part work by David Bruce with instructions for dance moves, and other world music.

episodesByNumber.title: #3536:  A Modern Liederabend
episodesByNumber.tease: It's a modern liederabend, "song night," featuring vocal  &  choral music from Paola Prestini inspired by Kandinsky, chamber opera by Missy Mazzoli,  &  opera by MIT professor Tod Machover.

episodesByNumber.title: #3537: Pipes & Wind Instruments Aplenty
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to the pipes and flutes a-calling on this New Sounds program in music from Argentinian producer/DJ Chancha Via Circuito, music by Alaska-based John Luther Adams,  &  much more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3538: Mixed-Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear "Mixed Music" – a term coined by musician/composer Joseph C. Phillips Jr. - which is a blend of jazz improvisation and groove-based minimalism or other forms of composed music.

episodesByNumber.title: #3540: Cultural Collisions
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear cross-cultural music, including piano music based on traditional Indian raga scales, a Persian bagpiper and Syrian sax player, Ethiopian music from the Netherlands, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3541: Two Unconventional Orchestral Works
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music of vast scale and ravishing textures in works by the Icelandic composer Anna Thorvaldsdottir.  Also, listen to music by the Estonian composer Arvo Pärt – his "Tabula Rasa."

episodesByNumber.title: #3542: Nelson Mandela, In Memoriam
episodesByNumber.tease: In remembrance of Nelson Mandela, we'll revisit a studio session recorded on the occasion of Nelson Mandela's arrival in New York City in June of 1990, just months after being set free.

episodesByNumber.title: #3543: One on Ones: Duo Music
episodesByNumber.tease: It's an hour of duo music for this New Sounds with several one-on-one meetings of two musical minds. Hear all sorts of duos - from guitar and percussion to harpist and laptop.

episodesByNumber.title: #3544: Acoustic Music Inspired by Electronica
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to acoustic music inspired by electronica –IDM (intelligent dance music) to downtempo or ambient music – but completely performed on acoustic instruments on this New Sounds.

episodesByNumber.title: #3545: Music From the Dark Side
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music from the dark side, including music by Bryce Dessner played by Kronos Quartet along with music by the Irish choir Anúna performing Tenebrae in Gaelic, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3546: Yodels and Hockets
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music involving yodeling  &  the rhythmic technique called hocketing, featuring Roomful of Teeth  &  music by Merrill Garbus, Circle Songs by Bobby McFerrin,  &  music by Meredith Monk.

episodesByNumber.title: #3547: Music for Gamelan
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music that features the gamelan from the Royal Court Gamelan of Surakarta, Lou Harrison, Eberhard Schoener, and Gamelan Son of Lion.

episodesByNumber.title: #3548: Between Two Worlds
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music between two worlds: orchestra, choral, or chamber works which also embrace elements of pop, rock and electronic music. Hear music from Son Lux, Missy Mazzoli,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3550: New Music For Fiddles and Violins
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to various forms of music for violin and fiddle, incorporating folk traditions from the world over – like those of Scandinavia, Eastern Europe, and Scotland, to name a few.

episodesByNumber.title: #3551: John Schaefer's Annual Top Ten -2013 edition
#3553: Piano Plus - Mostly
episodesByNumber.tease: On this New Sounds program, piano music. Hear the piano in more and less traditional contexts, including a reworked version of Philip Glass's "Trilogy Sonata."

episodesByNumber.title: #3554: All Fours
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music for quartets, but not the usual two violins, viola, and cello. Rather, the guiding principle will be four musicians, playing everything from marimba to mandolin.

episodesByNumber.title: #3555: New Music for Clarinets
episodesByNumber.tease: Can't get enough clarinet? Hear music from David Krakauer, Beth Custer, Evan Ziporyn, Don Byron, Alan Batiste,  &  others.

episodesByNumber.title: #3556: Rhythms of Minimalism
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music in the minimalist vein from Chris Campbell, Kate Soper, Philip Glass, Emanuele E. Forni, and Chris Morphitis.

episodesByNumber.title: #3557: Percussion Plus
episodesByNumber.tease: New Sounds takes a beating tonight with music from Mantra Percussion, Steven Schick, TIGUE, Third Coast Percussion, David Van Tieghem, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3558: Mountain Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Spend some time in the Swiss Alps, Andes, and the Himalayan, Appalachian, and Sierra Mountains. Music from Wu Man, Gyuto Monks Tantric Choir, Eberhard Schoener, Inti Illimani, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3559: Highlights from 2014 NY Guitar Festival Marathon
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to highlights from the 2014 New York Guitar Festival Marathon concert, featuring music from both North and South America, recorded at Merkin Hall.

episodesByNumber.title: #3561: Music for Cathedrals, Part 1
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to the acoustic  &  electronic works that make use of cathedral acoustics, or are inspired by the soaring architecture of some of the great old cathedrals, Part 1.

episodesByNumber.title: #3562: Music for Cathedrals, Part 2
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to more music written for, about, and in cathedrals on this New Sounds (part 2 of 2,) with music by Joby Talbot which musically describes one of Spain's great cathedrals - Léon.

episodesByNumber.title: #3563: New Sounds Live: The Hilliard Ensemble Farewell
episodesByNumber.tease: From the New Sounds Live concerts, recorded at the Metropolitan Art Museum's Temple of Dendur in 2014, listen to the four male voices of The Hilliard Ensemble from their farewell tour.

episodesByNumber.title: #3564: Synesthesia
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music that was imagined in colors, by composers who have synesthesia, a rare neurological phenomenon where two or more of their senses cross wires and connect in an unusual way.

episodesByNumber.title: #3565: World Music With a Side of Dylan
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear world music from Iran, Mali, Algeria, Egypt, and Benin, including a celebration of African women from Angelique Kidjo,  &  selections from a world music tribute to Bob Dylan.

episodesByNumber.title: #3566: Love Songs Around the World
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to an hour of lovely songs in Spanish, Portuguese, Cajun-French, Hebrew, Bengali, and multi-level Iranian love/devotional poetry for this New Sounds program.

episodesByNumber.title: #3567:  Far - Music About Distance
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music that deals with distance from Francis White  &  her work, "far, still," for Seattle's Solaris Vocal Ensemble, plus Eve Beglarian's "I am writing to you from a far-off country."

episodesByNumber.title: #3568: Percussive Roots, New Routes
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds program, hear music that begins with a percussive idea, maybe even a traditional one, but then ends up someplace else. Hear works by Glenn Kotche, Dosh,  &  Frisk Frugt

episodesByNumber.title: #3569: Norwegian New Music, with Tord Gustavsen Quartet
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, listen to new music from Norway, including a live set by the serene and transcendent Tord Gustavsen Quartet.

episodesByNumber.title: #3570: New Music From England
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear new music from England, including off-world music from "The Red Book," the 2nd record by global chamber/world music group Penguin Café. Plus, music by the Unthanks  &  Jocelyn Pook.

episodesByNumber.title: #3572: Folk-Inspired Ballads, Male Edition
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to folk-inspired ballads, featuring male voices, from the Gloaming  &  "Hirta Songs," by Alistair Roberts and Robin Robertson - songs about remote Scottish archipelago of St. Kilda.

episodesByNumber.title: #3573: Brass Band Music (for Mardi Gras!)
episodesByNumber.tease: It's a brass band takeover -rooted in New Orleans second line- with Youngblood Brass Band (Madison, WI), Revolutionary Snake Ensemble (Boston)  &  MarchFourth Marching Band (Portland, OR.)

episodesByNumber.title: #3574: Unusual Uses of the Voice
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to other ways of making music with the human voice, specifically, music that occupies the space between speech and song by the late American composer Robert Ashley,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3575: Reeds Lead
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear ensemble music led by wind instruments like clarinet, saxophone, and bass clarinet, featuring jazz-rock-electronica quartet Get the Blessing, and music by sax player Sarah Manning.

episodesByNumber.title: #3576: From the Bang On A Can Founders
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music from the founding composers of New York's Bang on a Can organization: David Lang, Michael Gordon, and Julia Wolfe.

episodesByNumber.title: #3577: Ballads From the UK - Female Voices
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to beautiful and haunting English  &  Scottish ballads sung by women including the Furrow Collective, English vocalist June Tabor and the Philadelphia group Espers, to name a few.

episodesByNumber.title: #3578: NY-based Indie Classical Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear New York-based "indie classical" music, including "Thunder Lay Down in the Heart," a work by violinist/composer/sound engineer Christopher Tignor, This Will Destroy You,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3579: Abandoned Cities
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to a series of works about abandoned cities and towns. Hear more "Hirta Songs," from Scotland, Hauschka's "Abandoned City,"  &  Brooklyn Rider/Kayhan Kalhor's "Silent City."

episodesByNumber.title: #3581: Percussion Ensembles
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music for percussion ensemble, including music by Chicago-based composer Mason Bates from his record, "Stereo Is King," music by David T. Little, Susie Ibarra,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3582: Music From the Near East and North Africa
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music from the Near East  &  North Africa by Moroccan Gnawa musician Hassan Hakmoun, Paris-based Palestinian oud player Adnan Joubran,  &  Tunisian percussionist Imed Alibi.

episodesByNumber.title: #3583: With Kent Tritle
episodesByNumber.tease: Kent Tritle, leader of Musica Sacra  &  music director at St. John the Divine, joins John Schaefer.  Hear choral music by Meredith Monk and Minnesota-based composer Jocelyn Hagen,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3584: New Releases, March 2014
episodesByNumber.tease: It's the most wonderful time of the month - the showcasing of new releases! On this New Sounds program, listen to the pick of the piles, the cream of the crop.

episodesByNumber.title: #3585: Ecstatic Music Festival 2014: Timo Andres Work Songs
episodesByNumber.tease: From the New Sounds Live Concerts, hear selections from "Work Songs" by Timo Andres for 3 voices, 2 guitars, keyboard, accordion, and piano. Plus, songs by Becca Stevens  &  Ted Hearne.

episodesByNumber.title: #3586: Bang on a Can PCF Concert 2014
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to portions of the Bang on a Can People's Commissioning Fund Concert 2014 –with works by Julia Wolfe  &  David Lang,  &  Brooklyn-based electroacoustic composer Daniel Wohl.

episodesByNumber.title: #3587: Electroacoustic Chamber Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music by Serbian Aleksandra Vrebalov written for ETHEL, along with selections from Vijay Iyer's "Mutations I-X,"  &  a work for steel cello  &  bow chimes by Heiner Goebbels.

episodesByNumber.title: #3588: Women of Classic Greek Drama in Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to Greek composer and vocalist Eleni Karaindrou's musical score for a modern adaptation of the ancient Greek tragedy of Medea on this New Sounds.

episodesByNumber.title: #3589: Medieval + Electronic = ?
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear ecstatic melodies from the 12th century German abbess Hildegard of Bingen in a contemporary context. Listen to a version of her "O Viridissima Virga," by Bora Yoon  &  others.

episodesByNumber.title: #3590: Musical Landscapes
episodesByNumber.tease: Journey through musical landscapes from the likes of Karen Tanaka, Jim Fox, and 2014 Pulitzer Prize-winning composer John Luther Adams on this New Sounds show.

episodesByNumber.title: #3591: Ecstatic Music Festival 2014: Buke and Gase, So Percussion
episodesByNumber.tease: From the New Sounds Live concert series, listen to a 2014 Ecstatic Music Festival collaborative pairing of Buke and Gase, together with So Percussion.

episodesByNumber.title: #3593: Voice & Electronics
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music for voice and electronics, including "Silver Threads," a song cycle written for soprano Mellissa Hughes by Jacob Cooper, music by Bora Yoon, Julianna Barwick  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3594: A World of World Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear a world of world music, some drawing on Indian classical music, others on the maracatu band music of northeast Brazil, along with music from a Tunisian percussionist  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3595: Music Based on Eastern European Singing
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear the original recording of The Mystery of the Bulgarian Voices, plus music from Ukraine's Mariana Sadovska with Kitka, from their phenomenal record "The Rusalka Cycle," and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3596: Flashback Friday: New &
episodesByNumber.tease: Enjoy a flashback show with music by Jean-Michel Jarre from the 1970's; his eight-part suite, "Equinoxe," plus music by Manuel Göttsching named after the opening chess move, 'E2-E4.'

episodesByNumber.title: #3597: Music Inspired By Painters, Part 1
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to the first of a three-part series of music dealing with paintings and/or painters. Listen to violinist Tracy Silverman's "O'Keeffe: Red Poppy,"  "Picasso: Guernica,"  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3598: Music Inspired By Painters, Part 2
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear pieces inspired by Matisse, Joao Miro, Max Ernst, Vermeer, and even the famous Paleolithic cave paintings in Lascaux, France.

episodesByNumber.title: #3599: Music Inspired By Painters, Part 3
episodesByNumber.tease: For this third and final show in our series of music inspired by painters and their paintings, listen to an hour of works after the painter, Mark Rothko (1903 -1970) and his paintings.

episodesByNumber.title: #3600: Hybrid Jazz-ish Ensembles
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear hybrid groups that use jazzy instruments, but throw in traditional folk, chamber music, and a splash of rock, like the Swiss quintet pommelHORSE  &  London-based trumpeter Yazz Ahmed.

episodesByNumber.title: #3601: Between Rock and Classical
episodesByNumber.tease: Music that falls into the cracks between rock and classical, between popular music and contemporary chamber music.

episodesByNumber.title: #3602: Post-Rock/Post-Classical
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear post-classical or post-rock from Bryce Dessner, his "Raphael," along with orchestral music with an ambient drone approach in "Virginia," a large work from duo Stars of the Lid.
tags: a winged victory for the sullen

episodesByNumber.title: #3603: Jazz & Blues Melting Pot
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear another musical melting pot program, from a jazz/blues angle with Norwegian blues guitarist Stein Ornheim, Brazilian-Moroccan musical collision Hijaz, an oud-piano dialogue  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3604: Twilight Songs
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music that inhabits a twilit world on this New Sounds, featuring a set from the remarkable Irish-American quintet The Gloaming. Plus, music from the Unthanks  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3605: New Releases, May 2014 & Pete M. Wyer
#3606: Electronic Songs
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear electronic songs involving voice, sometimes layered with more layers of keyboards  &  electronics, and other instruments, featuring Laurie Anderson's "O Superman," and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3607: Music for Dulcimer and Zither
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear new music for dulcimers and zithers, featuring hammer dulcimer  &  other folk instruments by Julia Wolfe in her work "Steel Hammer," based on the 19th C. folk legend John Henry.

episodesByNumber.title: #3609: Music for Big Bands
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear recent big band recordings, like that of the German-based Monika Roscher Bigband, and New York-based 17-piece Darcy James Argue's Secret Society on this New Sounds.

episodesByNumber.title: #3610: Music From the 7 Celtic Nations
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, listen to music from the seven Celtic nations  Ireland, Scotland, Wales, France (Brittany), England (Cornwall), Isle of Man and Spain (Galicia).

episodesByNumber.title: #3611:  From New Sounds Live
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear excerpts from almost 30 years of New Sounds Live concerts, with music by Jacob TV performed by ETHEL, Hungarian folk band Muzsikas, the adventurous jazz of the Bad Plus,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3613: New Sounds Live: The Gloaming in The Greene Space (Part 1)
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear Irish-American "Supergroup" The Gloaming, recorded at our Jerome L. Greene Space in June 2014. Their collective sound creates a haunted world where Celtic music meets minimalism.

episodesByNumber.title: #3614:  Fingerpicking Guitar and "Dark Was the Night"
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music that grows out of American blues and folk, with a whole lot of fingerpicking guitar, including music from the great blues guitarist, Blind Willie Johnson, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3615: Drummers / Bandleaders
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear all sorts of drummer-led bands, including music from composer/percussionist Susie Ibarra, alternative/avant-jazzer Jim Black, Afrobeat progenitor/drummer Tony Allen  &  many others.

episodesByNumber.title: #3616: New Sounds Live: The Gloaming in The Greene Space (Part 2)
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear The Gloaming, comprised of gifted Irish and Irish-American heavyweights, in their riveting blend of traditional Celtic meets minimalism and New York downtown music. (Part 2 of 2.)

episodesByNumber.title: #3617: New Approaches to Shape Note Hymns
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music that is rooted in shape-note singing from the 19th century, with tunes  &  texts directly taken from Protestant hymnals,  &  other works originally notated in "shape notes."

episodesByNumber.title: #3618: Human/Avian Collaborations
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear works that employ birdsongs, including Rautavaara's "Cantus Arcticus" for orchestra  &  birds on tape, music for L.A.-based group Wild Up,  &  big band post-jazz by John Hollenbeck.

episodesByNumber.title: #3619: Non-Classical Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to some non-classical music by classically-trained musicians, including music from Shara Worden/My Brightest Diamond, acoustic music quartet The 442s,  &  cellist Erik Friedlander.

episodesByNumber.title: #3620: Electric Guitarist/Composers
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, dig into a variety of sounds from electric guitarist/composers, like the ambient electronic texture of Noveller to the pulsing minimalist shimmer of Empyrean Atlas.

episodesByNumber.title: #3621: Lutes Around the World
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music from members of the lute family - like Greek bouzouki, Russian balalaika, and Chinese pipa, along with music from the Afghan-American rubab master Quraishi.

episodesByNumber.title: #3622: With Ben Neill
episodesByNumber.tease: Composer, performer, producer, and inventor of the mutantrumpet, Ben Neill,presents music from his project "Manitoga" for this New Sounds program.

episodesByNumber.title: #3623: Music for Heart & Breath, plus Zion80
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear Richard Reed Parry's "Quartet for Heart and Breath" by both yMusic and Kronos Quartet. Also, listen to Zion80, a horn-driven Jewish Afrobeat party band led by guitarist Jon Madof.

episodesByNumber.title: #3624: Choral and/or Electronic Works
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear electronic music informed by the sounds of choral music and the mirror image, blurring the boundaries between both, including music by Qasim Naqvi of the band Dawn of Midi  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3625: Stories in Music
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, listen to music that tells stories with works like "Casino" by composer and politician Phillip Bimstein, plus music by Laurie Anderson, David Byrne, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3626: Female Voices
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music for female voices, very often layers of voice on this New Sounds program. Hear the New York- and Sendai, Japan-based composer Aya Nishina's work, "Flora", and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3627: Cross Cultural Music From the Indian Subcontinent
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear a blend of western music  &  musicians from North  &  South India and/or Pakistan, featuring guitarist Warren Cuccurullo  &  the late Hindustani musician Ustad Sultan Khan, among others.

episodesByNumber.title: #3628: Choral Music, Gamelan-Style
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music for chorus, "gamelan-style" on this New Sounds, including the gamelan-based wonder that is "Don Ah," from "Gamel," by Japanese drummer/composer Yoshimi's outfit OOIOO,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3629: Chamber Pop/Art Songs
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, listen to orchestral and chamber music songs that don't fit comfortably into the "indie" rock world, like music from My Brightest Diamond.

episodesByNumber.title: #3630: Chamber Music With Turntables and Electronics
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear a different kind of chamber music, one that includes turntables (Randall Woolf), or the found sounds of industry from a factory in Germany (A. Gosfield) on this New Sounds.

episodesByNumber.title: #3631: West Meets West Africa
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear western music together with music of West Africa, as in music from the Beirut-born Raja Kassis or the Jewish Afro-beat party band Zion80, led by Jon Madof, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3632: Small Ensembles, Big Sounds
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to small ensembles with a big sound for this New Sounds show, featuring music from a James Blackshaw film score, and recent work from Bing  &  Ruth.

episodesByNumber.title: #3633:  Being Dufay, And Machaut
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear an hour of re-imaginings of the music by 14th C. composer Guillaume de Machaut and 15th C. composer Guillaume Dufay on this New Sounds in works by Robert Sadin, and Samuel Blaser.

episodesByNumber.title: #3634: Music by Moondog
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music by the American composer Moondog, as well as re-inventions of his tunes by other ensembles like Hobocombo, Sylvain Rifflet  &  Jon Irabagon and Kronos Quartet.

episodesByNumber.title: #3635: New Looks at Old American Folksongs
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to arrangements of American folk music and their descendants for this New Sounds, including Julia Wolfe's "Steel Hammer" and new music by banjo duo Abigail Washburn  &  Béla Fleck.

episodesByNumber.title: #3636: New Music for Trombone
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear the trombone, sometimes by itself, sometimes in a world music setting, sometimes with electronics, and sometimes en masse for this New Sounds show.

episodesByNumber.title: #3637: "Indie Classical" and "Garage Chamber"
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear so-called "indie classical" works on this New Sounds - music which is at home in both the contemporary classical music world and the indie rock/pop music halls.

episodesByNumber.title: #3638: Psychedelic World Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to world music that veers into psychedelic territory on this New Sounds, with Native-American inspired percussive drone music and Afrobeat from Brazil in music by Bixiga 70.

episodesByNumber.title: #3639: Piano Dances
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to dances for the piano, including works by G.I. Gurdjieff, Francesco Tristano, John Adams, and Tim Hecker on this New Sounds.

episodesByNumber.title: #3640: More All Over the World Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music that brings together sounds of the Mediterranean, Southern Italy, and Morocco, with the sounds of Balkans and Scandinavia, including music from NY-based Dálava.

episodesByNumber.title: #3641: Music for Bowed Strings
episodesByNumber.tease: On this New Sounds, music for violin, cello, and the 10-stringed Hardanger d'Amore, with music from Irish cellist Kate Ellis, and the duo of Caoimhín Ó Raghallaigh  &  Dan Trueman.

episodesByNumber.title: #3642:  New Music From Scandinavia
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, listen to new music from Scandinavia, including folk-jazz from the Swedish-Norwegian-English sextet FatDog, who draw from the traditions of Scandinavia and Britain.

episodesByNumber.title: #3643: New Releases, September 2014
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to the cream of the crop! It's the best of the new releases that have invaded the New Sounds library, including this year's Pulitzer Prize-winning work, "Become Ocean."

episodesByNumber.title: #3644: Another World Music Edition
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, listen to world music, including music from the Argentinian DJ and producer Chancha via Circuito, new music by Indo-Canadian singer Kiran Ahluwalia, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3645: John Luther Adams: Become Ocean
episodesByNumber.tease: On tonight's New Sounds, immerse yourself in John Luther Adams's Become Ocean, a forty-two-minute piece for large orchestra which won the Pulitzer Prize for Music in 2014.

episodesByNumber.title: #3646: 25 Years Of Real World Records I
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to the first of our two part celebration of Peter Gabriel's Real World record label, featuring music from around the globe: obscure folk chants, gospel, rock and/or classical.

episodesByNumber.title: #3647: 25 Years Of Real World Records II
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to the second in our two part celebration of Peter Gabriel's Real World record label, featuring music from around the globe: obscure folk chants, gospel, rock and/or classical.

episodesByNumber.title: #3648: Based on American Folk Songs
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music inspired by American folksong for this New Sounds, including tunes from Sam Amidon, Robert Plant, and Julia Wolfe's "Steel Hammer," about the legend of John Henry.

episodesByNumber.title: #3649: The New Music/Rock Music Connection
episodesByNumber.tease: This New Sounds program highlights the connection between new music and rock music, including music from the Steve Reich recording "Radio Rewrite," which takes on Radiohead songs.

episodesByNumber.title: #3650: From Speech to Song
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, listen to works that begin with speech, but incorporate sampling, delays, and other electronic manipulations, like Scott Johnson's "John Somebody" and others.

episodesByNumber.title: #3651: The Pixies : New Sounds-Style
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, hear Pixies songs arranged "New Sounds-Style" by everyone from Bang on a Can's marching band, Asphalt Orchestra, to Inuk throat singer Tanya Tagaq, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3652: Just Looping Strings
episodesByNumber.tease: Looped strings run through all three of the works on this New Sounds program, including Michael Harrison's "Just Ancient Loops" for Maya Beiser  &  "The Violin" by Anna Clyne/Josh Dorman.

episodesByNumber.title: #3653: With Paul Dresher
episodesByNumber.tease: Composer, electric guitarist, and inventor of the Quadracord, Paul Dresher, joins John Schaefer for this New Sounds program.

episodesByNumber.title: #3654: New Music from Berlin
episodesByNumber.tease: Berlin has been a global capital of electronic music for decades. In this New Sounds edition, John Schaefer brings us the latest music you might hear in the late hours in this city.

episodesByNumber.title: #3655: New Music for Didjeridu
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds program, listen to music for didgeridoo (also spelled didjeridoo) - the indigenous Australian drone wind instrument made out of a hollowed-out tree branch.

episodesByNumber.title: #3656: October 2014 New Releases
episodesByNumber.tease: John Schaefer carefully sorts through the stacks, bins, downloads and boatloads of new releases which have come across his desk over the past month to present the finest of the bunch.

episodesByNumber.title: #3657: Songs and Poems From Europe
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to songs and poems from Europe, including Polish and Albanian poetry set to post-jazz and neo-folk and music from the Swiss-Albanian singer Elina Duni.

episodesByNumber.title: #3658: New Sounds Live: Julia Wolfe's 'Steel Hammer' at Brookfield Place
episodesByNumber.tease: Recorded live from October 2014, the Bang On A Can All-Stars and vocalists Emily Eagan, Katie Geissinger, and Molly Quinn take on Wolfe's piece based on the legend of John Henry.

episodesByNumber.title: #3659: Sax Leads the Way
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear some sax players leading the way on this edition of New Sounds, including new music from sax player Tamar Osborn and her London-based Afro-Eastern-space-jazz band, Collocutor.

episodesByNumber.title: #3660: New Sounds Live: The Knights & Bryce Dessner
episodesByNumber.tease: From the New Sounds Live Concert Series, listen to new music from a collaboration between guitarist/composer Bryce Dessner and the flexible NY-based orchestral collective, The Knights.

episodesByNumber.title: #3661: New Music for Duos
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music from Xylouris White, Mary Lattimore  &  Jeff Zeigler, Jeffrey Zeigler (confusingly)  &  Jason Treuting, Piers Faccini  &  Vincent Segal  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3662: Music With Echoes of the Near East
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds show, listen to music with echoes of Turkey, Israel,  &  Egypt. Hear music from the French-born clarinetist Yom, Montreal-based chamber post-rock band Esmerine,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3663: Black Mountain Songs
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, John Schaefer talks with co-curators of "Black Mountain Songs," Richard Reed Parry and Bryce Dessner, and Brooklyn Youth Chorus Director Dianne Berkun-Menaker.

episodesByNumber.title: #3664: New Sounds Live: Tubular Bells
episodesByNumber.tease: From the New Sounds Live Concerts, hear a new arrangement of Mike Oldfield's Tubular Bells by guitarist Grey Mcmurray, with the Wordless Music Orchestra from Brookfield Place, Oct. 2014.

episodesByNumber.title: #3665: With The Touré-Raichel Collective
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, hear performances by Malian guitarist Vieux Farka Touré and Israeli pianist Idan Raichel, known as the Touré-Raichel Collective, plus other global acoustic music.

episodesByNumber.title: #3666: Orchestral and Electronic Music
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, hear electronic-inspired orchestral music from Ted Hearne and Anna Thorvaldsdottir, music from Ben Frost and Daníel Bjarnason, and a work from Brian Eno as well.

episodesByNumber.title: #3667: November 2014 New Releases
episodesByNumber.tease: John Schaefer's favorite releases from November featuring music by Philip Glass, Anthony Davis, Tomasz Trzcinski, Matt Skellenger, Trio Mediaeval, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3668: Music for Violin Plus
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear new music featuring violin on this New Sounds, including music by Irish fiddler/composer Adrian Hart,  &  selections from Anna Clyne's remarkable multimedia work, "The Violin."

episodesByNumber.title: #3669: Ambient Electroacoustic Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to an hour of ambient electro-acoustic music for this New Sounds program, with music by American composer Huck Hodge and English composer/producer Jon Hopkins.

episodesByNumber.title: #3670: Music for Choir and Percussion
episodesByNumber.tease: Music for choir and percussion by Andrew Byrne, Toru Takemitsu, Daniel Lentz, and Anna Thorvaldsdottir.

episodesByNumber.title: #3671: Empyrean Atlas, Live
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear guitars aplenty, from a performance by the Afro-poppy minimalist band Empyrean Atlas to Noveller's looped soundscapes, and works by Robert Fripp and the League of Crafty Guitarists.

episodesByNumber.title: #3672: Piano-Based New Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to piano-based new music, including works by both Woodkid  &  Max Richter, Piano Etudes by Don Byron, performed by Lisa Moore,  &  music by Polish composer/pianist Tomasz Trzcinski.

episodesByNumber.title: #3673: The Human Element
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear musical collaborations between "human" and "machine" sounds, including "Surface Image," a Vicky Chow-commissioned work by Tristan Perich for piano and 1-bit electronics  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3674: Clarinet-Centric New Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear new music for clarinets, including music from "Orphic Machine" by clarinetist/composer Ben Goldberg, space-jazz from Belgium, music by Derek Bermel  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3675: New Music for Banjo and Mandolin
episodesByNumber.tease: New music for banjo and mandolin from the Punch Brothers, Tony Trischka, Avi Avital, Ellipsis, Béla Fleck  &  Abigail Washburn, Jake Schepps, and Yo-Yo Ma.

episodesByNumber.title: #3676: New Music for Hardanger Fiddle
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to new music for Hardanger fiddle, including a post-rock drone band, world music, electroacoustic music, and even an Irish-American duet for the traditional Norwegian instrument.

episodesByNumber.title: #3677: Music, More Music for Christmas
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music of the season this Christmas, New-Sounds Style, with banjo, zither and theremin, piano insides, plus viola and electronics...in the service of some holiday classics.

episodesByNumber.title: #3678: New Music for 2015
episodesByNumber.tease: For this last show of 2014, look ahead to music due out in 2015. Listen to synthesizer music inspired by Euclidian geometry by Kaitlyn Aurelia Smith, banjo music by Jake Schepps  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3679: December 2014 New Releases
episodesByNumber.tease: For this show, we're looking back at some of the records that came into the New Sounds library in late 2014.

episodesByNumber.title: #3680: New Sounds Year In Review: Staff Picks
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to new music records from 2014, as picked by the New Sounds Staff: Fall Intern Emma Munger, Temporary Producer Isabel Kim, and the New Sounds All-Purpose Assistant Caryn Havlik.

episodesByNumber.title: #3681: Year in Review 2014: John Schaefer's Top 10
episodesByNumber.tease: John Schaefer presents his Top 10 new music releases of 2014. Listen to music by an Icelandic electro-acoustic composer, a Korean-American composer, a chamber-jazz-rock band,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3682: The Art of Tom Waits
episodesByNumber.tease: On this program, we go boldly where we've never gone before: into the art of Tom Waits - a whole hour of his distinctive voice and musical soundworld.

episodesByNumber.title: #3683: Mediterranean and Near Eastern Roots
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music which seems to look to the Silk Road and the passage of people and cultures over that trade route, with music from the Louis Sclavis Quartet record, "Silk and Salt Melodies."

episodesByNumber.title: #3684: Classics Recomposed
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear variations on, recompositions of, and even electronic treatments added to romantic, baroque  &  medieval works on this New Sounds.

episodesByNumber.title: #3685: Blues-Based Guitar Works
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to Songhai guitar music from Malian Samba Touré, American-rooted Moroccan-flavored blues by Sir Richard Bishop, and Mississippi blues from the duo 75 Dollar Bill. That, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3686: New Music for String Quartet
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear unusual music for string quartet, as Australian composer Andrew Byrne uses the string quartet as a percussion instrument in his work called "Striking,"  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3687: Alt-Marching Bands & Other Brass
episodesByNumber.tease: There's "freak" marching band music for this show from Mucca Pazza, and brass band music from Red Baraat, La Fanfare Couche-Tard, Breakdown Brass,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3688: Asian Voices
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to Asian voices on this New Sounds from Tibetan devotional singer Yungchen Lhamo, the Mongolian bluegrass/folk-rock band Hanggai, the Wulu Bunun people of Taiwan, and others.

episodesByNumber.title: #3689: Cinematic Instrumental Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear cinematic instrumental music from the English composer/vocalist Donna McKevitt, pianist/producer Chilly Gonzales, Olafur Arnalds' score to the British series "Broadchurch,"  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3690: January 2015 New Releases
episodesByNumber.tease: It's that time of the month again for the new releases show. John Schaefer carefully sorts through all of the submissions from the past month to present a bunch of percussive choices.

episodesByNumber.title: #3691: Gamelan Plus
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to works that include gamelan, but take a more western approach, including music by Barbara Benary/Gamelan Son of Lion and composer/sax player and bagpiper Matthew Welch.

episodesByNumber.title: #3692: Music from Eastern Europe
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music from Eastern Europe on this New Sounds, including music from the Czech violinist/violinist Iva Bittová, the Polish hardcore-folk outfit Warsaw Village Band, and others.

episodesByNumber.title: #3693: Electronic or Acoustic?
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear electronic or acoustic or electro-acoustic chamber music from Bing and Ruth, Missy Mazzoli  &  Victoire, Christopher Cerrone, a score by Jon Opstad, and an early work by John Adams.

episodesByNumber.title: #3694: Music for Jim Jarmusch Films
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music derived from Jim Jarmusch films: by Jarmusch himself and his instrumental bands, and music by Tom Waits, jazz-inflected music by John Lurie,  &  Ethio-jazz by Mulatu Astatke.

episodesByNumber.title: #3695: Voices of the Mediterranean
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear Mediterranean voices from Italy, Portugal, Algeria  &  Morocco, featuring flamenco singer Silvia Perez Cruz from the Blancanieves soundtrack, Lebanese singer Yasmine Hamdan,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3696: With Jóhann Jóhannsson
episodesByNumber.tease: The Icelandic-born, Berlin-based composer Jóhann Jóhannsson visits our studio to introduce portions of his Oscar-nominated score to the film "The Theory of Everything",  &  other works.

episodesByNumber.title: #3697: Australian Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music from Australia with everything from didjeridu to a ballet score, including "Practical Mechanics," a 5-part work by composer Chris Perren for his septet, Nonsemble.

episodesByNumber.title: #3698: Unusual Waltzes and Tangos
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear an hour of unusual waltzes and tangos, from Korean komungo music to a waltz by Philip Glass to music by Yugoslav Goran Bregovic.

episodesByNumber.title: #3699: Bang on a Can PCF Works
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to works from the Bang on a Can People's Commissioning Fund, from Dan Deacon, Christine Southworth, Daniel Wohl,  &  Marc Mellits, all played by the Bang on a Can All-Stars.

episodesByNumber.title: #3700: Arctic Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear arresting new music for Inuit throat singer Tanya Tagaq  &  Kronos Quartet by Canadian Derek Charke - his epic "Tundra Songs." Also, music by Tanya Tagaq, Ben Frost  &  Paola Prestini.

episodesByNumber.title: #3701: New Releases February 2015
episodesByNumber.tease: Brand new music by saxman Colin Stetson  &  violinist Sarah Neufeld, the Northumbrian folk phenoms The Unthanks, Scottish band Treacherous Orchestra,  &  Malian music from the BKO Quintet.

episodesByNumber.title: #3702: Music Around the Globe
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear global music from Italy, India, Egypt, Tunisia and Mali, featuring the choir Finno-Balkan Voices, a French-Jewish Chinese duo, African blues guitarist Boubacar Traoré, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3703: Rewriting the Classics
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music based on or inspired by classic works of Beethoven, Mozart, Chopin, and J.S. Bach, including Michael Gordon's "ReWriting Beethoven's Seventh Symphony" and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3704: New Sounds Live: Blancanieves
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear the Wordless Music Orchestra perform Alfonso Vilallonga's score for the Snow-White-as-bullfighter silent film Blancanieves (2012), recorded live at Brookfield Place from Feb. 2015.

episodesByNumber.title: #3705: Spring Awakenings?
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to spring-themed music from Taiwan's A Moving Sound, Max Richter recomposing Vivaldi, and Meredith Monk's "Songs of Ascension," just because.

episodesByNumber.title: #3706: Various Electroacoustic Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear electroacoustic music by Dublin-based Seán Mac Erlaine and Australian-born, London-based Leah Kardos. Plus, music from NY-based GABI, cellist Julia Kent, and Bing  &  Ruth.

episodesByNumber.title: #3707: New Sounds Live: ETHEL, John King, & Kaki King
episodesByNumber.tease: From the Ecstatic Music Festival, recorded at Merkin Hall, we present a three-pronged collaboration of composer John King, guitarist Kaki King, and the string quartet ETHEL.

episodesByNumber.title: #3708: With Max Richter
episodesByNumber.tease: German keyboardist, composer, and producer Max Richter joins John Schaefer in the studio to present selections from Max Richter's recordings from the set, "Retrospective,"  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3709: With Missy Mazzoli
episodesByNumber.tease: Composer, keyboardist and bandleader Missy Mazzoli joins John Schaefer to introduce selections from her recent recording, "Vespers for a New Dark Age." And more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3710: New Releases, March 2015
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear Cameroonian dance rhythms with jazz feels from Ajoyo and music from Ibeyi, twin sisters whose music has elements of Yoruba culture. Plus, new music from Angelique Kidjo  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3711: New Sounds Live: Terry Riley @ 80
episodesByNumber.tease: From the Ecstatic Music Festival, recorded at Merkin Hall, Marco Benevento, Travis Laplante, Emily Wells, Lorna Dune  &  Gyan Riley mark minimalist composer Terry Riley's 80th birthday.

episodesByNumber.title: #3712: West and Central Africa
episodesByNumber.tease: Today's New Sounds features contemporary music from West and Central Africa. Traditional African rhythms combine with creative uses of semi-broken electronics, and energetic choruses.

episodesByNumber.title: #3713: New Music from Ireland Part 1
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to a whole week of shows surveying the Irish new music landscape to mark the 100th anniversary of the Easter Rising. In Part 1, John talks to Cork-based composer Irene Buckley.

episodesByNumber.title: #3714: New Music from Ireland Part 2
episodesByNumber.tease: John Schaefer travels to Ireland for a series dedicated to Irish composers. In this second episode, John talks to composers Ronan Guilfoyle and Grainne Mulvey in Dublin.

episodesByNumber.title: #3715: New Music from Ireland Part 3
episodesByNumber.tease: Continue exploring the new music of Ireland, with composer Jonathan Nangle, who explains how electronics and silence factor into his compositions, plus organ works by David Bremner.

episodesByNumber.title: #3716: GABI and 'Sympathy'
episodesByNumber.tease: John Schaefer sits down with composer/singer GABI to discuss her striking album "Sympathy." Enter an immersive vocal world as we listen to some of her experimental songs.

episodesByNumber.title: #3717: Celebrating Earth Day
episodesByNumber.tease: New Sounds celebrates Earth Day, featuring composers who use the sounds of the natural world to make music that belongs not just to humanity, but to the whole planet.
tags: a winged victory for the sullen

episodesByNumber.title: #3718: New Music from Ireland Part 4
episodesByNumber.tease: New Sounds returns to Ireland for another foray into the country's contemporary music scene. John Schaefer sits down with Derry-based Neil Burns and Belfast-based Greg Caffrey.

episodesByNumber.title: #3719: New Music from Ireland Part 5
episodesByNumber.tease: In the fifth installment of this series of new music featuring Irish composers, John Schaefer talks to composer Linda Buckley in Dublin.

episodesByNumber.title: #3720: New Releases, April 2015
episodesByNumber.tease: John Schaefer combs through all the CD stacks, SoundCloud files, and digital releases that came through this April and plays some of the best of the best.

episodesByNumber.title: #3721: New Music from Ireland Part 6
episodesByNumber.tease: In the sixth edition of our New Music from Ireland series, John Schaefer talks to Belfast-based Piers Hellawell, Bernadette Comac, and Deirdre McKay about making music after hard times.

episodesByNumber.title: #3722: The Altered State of the Piano
episodesByNumber.tease: There's no Chopin or Rachmaninov in this all-piano edition of the show. Instead, hear music from Moon Ate the Dark to Oliver Messiaen, along with works by George Crumb  &  John Corigliano.

episodesByNumber.title: #3723: New Music from Ireland Part 7
episodesByNumber.tease: New Sounds returns to Ireland for the finale of a seven-part series of Irish New Music, featuring Cork-based composers Karen Power and John Godfrey, along with the Quiet Music Ensemble.

episodesByNumber.title: #3724: With The Cellar and Point
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear the downtown-y garage-chamber jazz-tronica from The Cellar and Point. The septet performs their tunes live in the studio and chats with John Schaefer for this New Sounds.

episodesByNumber.title: #3725: With Poppy Ackroyd
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear an exclusive interview with Brighton-based pianist, violinist, and composer Poppy Ackroyd, and music from her record, "Feathers," recorded on location in London in April of 2015.

episodesByNumber.title: #3726: Music Based on World Dance Traditions
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear the rhythms and dance traditions from Spain's Basque region in stomping accordion music by Kepa Junkera  &  vocal group Sorginak, plus Greek-Balkan, and French-Canadian music to boot.

episodesByNumber.title: #3727: Post-Minimalist Piano Works
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to "The Clearing," from Kentucky-based pianist  &  composer Rachel Grimes (formerly of Rachel's.) It's chamber-rock, with processing and uses strings, harp, piano, woodwinds  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3728: With Composer Jon Opstad
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music by London-based composer Jon Opstad, who has worked in film, dance, and television ("Black Mirror") and new music from his forthcoming record, "In a Different Light."  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3729: Man Ray Films, Music by SQÜRL
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear live recordings of world-premiere scores for Man Ray films, composed  &  performed by SQÜRL, in duo form, who are filmmaker/multi-instrumentalist Jim Jarmusch  &  drummer Carter Logan.

episodesByNumber.title: #3730: "No Man Is An Island" & Other Music Inspired by John Donne Poetry
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music inspired by 17th century English poet  &  philosopher John Donne, from Russian pianist/composer Anton Batagov, Norwegian pianist Ketil Bjornstad, Van Morrison,  &  Tarwater.

episodesByNumber.title: #3731: Next Wave of British Folk
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to musicians from British Isles take new approaches to the old songs, along with new folk-steeped compositions from Lau, the Unthanks, Spiro, Oliva Chaney,  &  Sam Lee.

episodesByNumber.title: #3732: New Releases, May 2015
episodesByNumber.tease: Sample new music by ShoutHouse, a collaboration involving composer/pianist Will Healy, a classical string section, two rappers, a jazz vocalist and drummer, and a Balkan clarinetist.

episodesByNumber.title: #3733: Bang On A Can All-Stars 2015 PCF Concert
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear commissioned works by Wilco's Glenn Kotche, Jace Clayton (aka DJ/rupture) and Irish composer Donnacha Dennehy from the 2015 Bang on a Can People's Commissioning Fund Concert.

episodesByNumber.title: #3734: "Indie Classical": Indie Chamber Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear new indie chamber works from NYC-based NOW Ensemble  &  the Australian Nonsemble. Plus, music by composer/bandleader Becca Stevens, from her  captivating record, "Perfect Animal."

episodesByNumber.title: #3735: Expansive Guitar-scapes
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear works that create atmospheric soundscapes through guitar loops for this New Sounds. Listen to music from the likes of Robert Fripp, David Torn, and the French artist, Colleen.

episodesByNumber.title: #3736: Music for Voices, Strings, and Voices & Strings
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to the vocal octet Roomful of Teeth from their recent, "Render," performing "Ascendant" by Australian-born Wally Gunn, music in Icelandic from Árstíðir and Yann Tiersen,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3737: Electronic Music Survey
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to electronic music from as far back as the 1970's by Laurie Spiegel, along with new music by Tyondai Braxton, from his recent "HIVE1" for this New Sounds.

episodesByNumber.title: #3738: New Sounds Live: ETHEL, John King & Kaki King, Part 2
episodesByNumber.tease: From the Ecstatic Music Festival, recorded at Merkin Hall, we present a three-pronged collaboration of composer John King, guitarist Kaki King, and the string quartet ETHEL  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3739: World Music, Then & Now
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to cross-cultural music from Codona's 1979 release and new music from the Bay area trio, Bolo, on this New Sounds. Plus, music for  &  by the late Ornette Coleman,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3740: Beyond the Pale (of Settlement)
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music from the Pale of Settlement, (Eastern Europe), featuring "Night Songs from a Neighboring Village" by Michael Alpert  &  Julian Kytasty, music by Andy Statman,  &  Frank London.

episodesByNumber.title: #3741: Big Works for Big Bands
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear big bands that draw from chamber music, science-fiction, ambient music, and the wonders of nature, including "The Thompson Fields" from Maria Schneider Orchestra and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3742: Terry Riley's In C, 80th Birthday Edition
episodesByNumber.tease: From the New Sounds Live Concert Series, with the Ecstatic Music Festival, listen to (most of) a celebratory 80th birthday performance of Terry Riley's "In C," recorded in March of 2015.

episodesByNumber.title: #3743: New Finnish-Norwegian Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music from the Norwegian-Finnish border, and music for Finnish folk-harp, the kantele - with music by half-Finnish/ half-Norwegian singer  &  master of the kantele, Sinikka Langeland.

episodesByNumber.title: #3744: Afrobeat, Afropop, & Afrofunk
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear Afropop and Afrobeat music from West Africa and elsewhere, including new music from Malian desert-blues queen Khaira Arby, recent music from Afrobeat band Antibalas,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3745: New Releases, June 2015
episodesByNumber.tease: Music from the Chatham Saxaphone Quartet, Laura Venditti, Bang On A Can All-Stars, Makaya Mccraven, and post-rock songs from Godspeed You! Black Emperor and Flying Saucer Attack.

episodesByNumber.title: #3746: "Songs of Experience": Music Inspired by Poetry of William Blake
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music inspired by English poet, painter, and printmaker William Blake, from Appalachian blues/roots music to experimental jazz and avant-garde electronica.

episodesByNumber.title: #3747: New Music From South America
episodesByNumber.tease: Sample music from Argentina, Peru, Columbia, and from Brazil from percussionists Simone Sou  &  Guilherme Kastrup, together as SouKast, work from Argentinian Chancha via Circuito  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3748: Chamber Music With an Electronic Boost
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear "electro-acoustic urban minimalism" from Finnish composer Juhani Nuorvala and Bang on a Can composer and co-founder Michael Gordon, along with works by Ireland's Linda Buckley.

episodesByNumber.title: #3749: Music With Found Voices
episodesByNumber.tease: Music with voices taken out of context by Anna Clyne and Julia Wolfe, auction samples by Ben Neill and Brian Irvine, and a tribute to Chuck Brown by Dick Connette. And cow sounds!

episodesByNumber.title: #3750: North Meets South
episodesByNumber.tease: North meets South, largely Europe meets Africa in music by French guitarist Titi Robin and Moroccan musician Mehdi Nassouli, the group Monoswezi,  & the collaborative group MaLithuanie.

episodesByNumber.title: #3751: Unusual Song Cycles
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to many unusual approaches to the song cycle, including music by Sarah Kirkland Snider from her "Unremembered," music by Pulitzer Prize-winner David Lang, "Zippo Songs,"  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3752: New Music for European Instruments
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music featuring unusual instruments from Belgium, Finland, Lithuania and Estonia, including music for traditional Finnish jouhikko by the Ilkka Heinonen Trio  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3753: Guitar Music, Mostly
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music for the guitar, rooted in the sounds of American folk music or jazz, like shimmering folk music by Meg Baird, and instrumental folk poetry by guitarist Sean Smith.

episodesByNumber.title: #3754: Cycling Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music created by a cyclical approach to composition, including works from Icelandic composer Maria Huld Markan Sigfúsdóttir for the chamber group Nordic Affect  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3755: Krautrock
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear German electronic music from the 1970s, with bands Tangerine Dream and Cluster, and solo pieces by their founders.

episodesByNumber.title: #3756: Composed Works, Unusual Settings
episodesByNumber.tease: Chamber music unlike that which you've heard before, featuring music by Eviyan, John Zorn played by Forro in the Dark, Christopher Tin, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3757: New Views of Old Folk Songs
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear folk songs from all over the world by artists such as Sam Lee, Kaia Kater, Sam Amidon, and the Furrow Collective.

episodesByNumber.title: #3758: New Releases July 2015
episodesByNumber.tease: A show of only new releases from July, featuring Sean Clancy, Jeremy Young and Aaron Martin, Peter Michael Hamel, Dave Soldier, and more

episodesByNumber.title: #3759: Wind and Water
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music made by wind and water, including "Bottles" by Bay-Area based electroacoustic duo Dirtwire, a work Daniel Lentz for wine glasses, and music for waterphone.

episodesByNumber.title: #3760: More Electronic Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to some electronic music on this New Sounds, including works for sax and electronics from Laura Venditti, trumpet and electronics from Dave Douglas featuring Shigeto, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3761: Moorish Music and its Influence
episodesByNumber.tease: Medieval Moorish music and contemporary music inspired by it, including tracks recorded live here in the New Sounds studio, feat. Jadid Ensemble, Rolf Lislevand, Hamza El Din, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3762: Chamber Music with Strange Instruments
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear chamber music with unusual instruments, including a work for the Partch instruments, music with Icelandic metallic percussion called klakabond, Tibetan singing bowls, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3763: New Sounds of Lesser-Heard Bowed Strings
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music for lesser-heard bowed string instruments – like the viola da gamba, cello, and viola d'amore - with multi-layered works by composer Zoe Keating and violist Jessica Meyer.

episodesByNumber.title: #3764: Brass Band Music Aplenty
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to brass band music from the world over, with Mexican banda music, Balkan brass, Ethio-jazz, and North African music for brass band plus traditional percussion instruments.

episodesByNumber.title: #3765: Post-Everything Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear instrumental rock or "post-rock" with strong undercurrents of folk, chamber music, minimalism, and some of the improvisatory elements of jazz from Tortoise, Matt Ulery, and others.

episodesByNumber.title: #3766: Sui-Generis Music - Or Not
episodesByNumber.tease: Music thought of as unique to its composer, until performed by someone else, such as music originally by Aphex Twin, Meredith Monk, Conlon Nancarrow, and Harry Partch.

episodesByNumber.title: #3767: "Unlimited," Gamelan, & Steve Reich
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear new music with elements of minimalism by Joseph C. Phillips, Jr., a Balinese gamelan work from Evan Ziporyn, and Steve Reich's seminal "Music for 18 Musicians" from Ensemble Signal.

episodesByNumber.title: #3768: Mid-Sized New Music Groups
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear new music from mid-sized new music groups like Now Ensemble, yMusic, chamber music sextet eighth blackbird, Robin Cox Ensemble, and Build.

episodesByNumber.title: #3769: New Releases August 2015
episodesByNumber.tease: New music from the month of August, including Ali Baba Cisse, TriBeCaStan, Decoda, and Eighth Blackbird.

episodesByNumber.title: #3770: Mostly Acoustic Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music for mostly acoustic instruments in unexpected combinations, like lute  &  electric guitar, alto saxophone  &  viola, or harp with bowed vibraphone, plus layered cellos  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3771: Modern Gnawa Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Explore some of the traditional Gnawa ritual music of Morocco, from New York-based Hassan Hakmoun, along with Cuban pianist Roberto Fonseca, and DC-based trio Les Rhinocéros, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3772: Remixing a Film, and a Biblical Book
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to large-scale remixes and re-imaginings, with a remix by DJ Spooky of a controversial silent film and a re-imagining of the Biblical Book of Ecclesiastes by Kitty Brazelton.

episodesByNumber.title: #3773: Choral Music from Latvia and Estonia
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to choral music from Latvia and Estonia in music by Estonian composers Veljo Tormis and Arvo Pärt, as well as works by Latvian composers Peteris Vasks and Maija Einfelde.

episodesByNumber.title: #3774: Electroacoustic Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to electroacoustic music from Berlin, Iceland, the U.K.,  &  New York, including the latest by NYC-based cellist  &  composer Julia Kent, new dance music from Jon Opstad  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3775: With TriBeCaStan, Live
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds episode, the global 10-piece ensemble TriBeCaStan brings their combination of world, funk, folk and jazz to our performance studio.

episodesByNumber.title: #3776: Electronic Music Classics Revisited
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to electronic music classics overlooked in recent years by pioneer Laurie Spiegel, Morton Subotnick and California E.A.R. Unit, and Ingram Marshall.

episodesByNumber.title: #3777: Music in the Dark
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music with darkness to it by Iceland's Anna Thorvaldsdottir, and New York-based composers Raphael Mostel, Tan Dun, and Christopher Cerrone.

episodesByNumber.title: #3778: Voices of the Near/Middle East
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to great voices in Arabic, from the Middle East and North Africa, including an Israeli cantor, a Lebanese Christian nun, a Syrian wedding singer and an Algerian Rai singer.

episodesByNumber.title: #3779: Folk Meets Minimalism: Violin and Viola Edition
episodesByNumber.tease: Folk meets minimalism, through both the violin and the viola for this New Sounds. Hear music from Estonian Maarja Nuut, Garth Knox, and Iva Bittová, among others.

episodesByNumber.title: #3780: New Releases, September 2015
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music for guitar and gamelan by Bill Alves, violin and resonator guitar by Paula Matthusen, and an ambitious solo piano arrangement of Massive Attack from Brad Mehldau.

episodesByNumber.title: #3781:  Anglo-American Folk Songs
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to an hour of Anglo-American Folk Songs, including music from Scotland's Furrow Collective, San Francisco-based Meg Baird,  &  the Boise, ID-based string-band trio, Hillfolk Noir.

episodesByNumber.title: #3782: Afropean Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music that is part of both African and European traditions with music from St. Germain, Damon Albarn and Toumani Diabate, Zap Mama, the late Hector Zazou, and Baka Beyond.

episodesByNumber.title: #3783: Music from Central Asia With Ustatshakirt Plus, Live
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, hear a traditional Kyrgyz music ensemble, Nurlanbek Nishanov  &  Ustatshakirt. Plus, more music of Central Asia and along the Silk Road.

episodesByNumber.title: #3784: With Jocelyn Pook
episodesByNumber.tease: English composer/violist/arranger/producer Jocelyn Pook joins John Schaefer to talk about her music for the Broadway play, King Charles III, and her song cycle, "Hearing Voices."

episodesByNumber.title: #3785: Music for Multiple Guitars and Aurelio, Live
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music for multiple guitars by Dither Quartet and the Sap Dream Electric Quartet, as well as Garifuna songwriter, singer, and guitarist Aurelio, performed live in-studio.

episodesByNumber.title: #3786: "Indie Classical" Works
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music by New York-based composers who are sometimes associated with "indie classical" - featuring works by Judd Greenstein, Annie Gosfield, Andy Akiho, and Angélica Negrón.

episodesByNumber.title: #3787: Jazz With a Groove
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear jazz with a groove, including piano trios with rock or hip-hop leanings, and/or with a whiff of minimalism, along with groove-driven jazz drawn from other places around the world.

episodesByNumber.title: #3788: Works for Voice and Electronics
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music for voice  &  electronics, including composer Ted Hearne's latest, The Source, based on the story of U.S. Army Private Manning, chamber opera by Frances White,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3789: Music for Trombone and Cello
episodesByNumber.tease: Explore the unexpected musical combination of cello and trombone: with electronics, in an African music setting from Blick Bassy, in a post-rock way, as a chamber pop song, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3790: Heart of a Dog, with Laurie Anderson
episodesByNumber.tease: Composer/storyteller/multi-instrumentalist Laurie Anderson joined John Schaefer upon the release of her palindromic new film, Heart of a Dog.

episodesByNumber.title: #3791:  American Gamelan Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear American gamelan music, including a work from Bay Area instrument builders  &  composers collective, the Lightbulb Ensemble, music for gamelan and guitar by Bill Alves,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3792: New Releases, October 2015
episodesByNumber.tease: New music for October, featuring Ghanian music via London,  &  Qawwali brass excellence sung in Hebrew from Junun, the Jonny Greenwood/Shye Ben Tzur/Rajasthan Express collaboration  &  film.

episodesByNumber.title: #3793: New Sounds Live Concerts 2015, Part 1
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music recorded in October 2015 at Brookfield Place, including a world premiere work by Angélica Negrón for the American Composers Orchestra  &  mechanical instruments,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3794: New Sounds Live Concerts 2015, Part 2: Multiple Guitars
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear Steve Reich's "Electric Counterpoint" for 13 electric guitars featuring Dither Quartet, plus Ben Verdery's "Ellis Island" from the New Sounds Live Concerts at Brookfield Place.

episodesByNumber.title: #3795: With the HKZ Trio, Live
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to the HKZ Trio -Hauschka, Samuli Kosminen, Jeffrey Zeigler- and their prepared piano, drums, cello, plus an array of live electronics,  create brand-new works in the studio.

episodesByNumber.title: #3796: New Music from Poland
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to new music  &  traditional music from Poland, with electroacoustic music by Jacaszek, centuries old rural Polish punk from RUTA, experimental-folk kitchen music by Sutari,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3797: Electronic and Electronically-Altered Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music that incorporates electronic sounds, along with purely electronic music, including the latest from the band, Battles, Squarepusher, and Kaitlyn Aurelia Smith.

episodesByNumber.title: #3798: Electro-Acoustica, With Piano & Not
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear electroacoustic music with piano-based works by Ludovico Einaudi, Moon Ate the Dark  &  Kevin Volans, plus non-piano-basd works by Paula Matthusen, Food,  &  From the Mouth of the Sun.
tags: from the mouth of the sun

episodesByNumber.title: #3799: "House Music": Music From Household Items
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear "House" music for this show: music made with things found around the house, like the rhythmic sounds of Matmos' washing machine, Paul Lansky's plates,  &  P. Bimstein's studio door.

episodesByNumber.title: #3800: A Cappella Around the World
