episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to a cappella music around the world, including works from Estonia, Ireland, Cuba, Bulgaria, Taiwan, Korea, Italy, Germany, and by American composer Bobby McFerrin.

episodesByNumber.title: #3801: Unusual Cross-Cultural Collaborations
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear unexpected musical dream-teams, with music from Jonny Greenwood (Radiohead), Shye Ben Tzur and The Rajasthan Express on Junun, plus brand new music from Raya Brass Band, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3802: A Whole Lotta Shakin' Goin' On
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to the highly rhythmic approach of the tremolando, or "trembling," shaking effect of the bow on the violin strings in music by Tristan Perich, Lois V. Vierk, and John Adams.

episodesByNumber.title: #3803: Tan Dun's "Water Passion," Live from the Temple of Dendur
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to Chinese-born American composer Tan Dan's "Water Passion after St. Matthew," recorded live at the Metropolitan Museum of Art's Temple of Dendur, conducted by the composer.

episodesByNumber.title: #3804: November 2015 New Releases
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear new releases from November, including a new recording of Brian Eno's "Discreet Music" from Ensemble Contact, instrumental rock from new music percussion trio TIGUE, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3805: New Music Based on Old Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear contemporary music built on much older musical structures - like music by 16th century composer, murderer, and Prince, Carlo Gesualdo, Bora Yoon's take on Hildegarde, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3806: Cross-Cultural Music of Many Stripes
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music from many different parts of the world, like an American group who looks to East Africa, an Irish group that looks to Indonesia, and a Brazilian Afrobeat band, to name a few.

episodesByNumber.title: #3807: Percussion-Heavy Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to percussion-based music from the Austin, TX-based Kraken Quartet, gamelan-driven Celtic-influenced work from composer Matthew Welch, and music from OOIOO, led by Yoshimi P-We.

episodesByNumber.title: #3808: Wordless Vocals
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear unusual uses of the voice in music by vocal octet Roomful of Teeth, along with music by Philip Glass, Meredith Monk, and Irish composer Michael McGlynn for Chanticleer.

episodesByNumber.title: #3809: Electronic and Electronically Enhanced Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear electronic music made by nonkeen, featuring Nils Frahm, a work by electric violist Martha Mooke, music by London-based Floating Points, sample Oneohtrix Point Never, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3810: World Music Tour Sampler
episodesByNumber.tease: Sample music from several corners of the world, including Anglo-Kenyan, Anglo-Indian collaborations and music from Argentinian producer Chancha via Circuito.

episodesByNumber.title: #3811: New Sounds Live Concerts 2015, Part 3
episodesByNumber.tease: Recorded in October 2015 at Brookfield Place, hear Alex Mincek's world premiere for the American Composers Orchestra vs. JACK Quartet, and David Lang's work for 121 guitars and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3812: Groove-Based Jazz
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music from Norway's doom jazz piano trio Splashgirl, trombonist/composer Jacob Garchik and his band of heroes, the quintet Ye Olde, along with Allison Miller's Boom Tic Boom.

episodesByNumber.title: #3813: New Sounds Live Concerts 2015: 'My City'
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear the world premiere of Judd Greenstein's "My City," by the ACO with DM Stith and The Crossing. It's a setting of two Whitman poems, "Mannahatta" and "Crossing Brooklyn Ferry."

episodesByNumber.title: #3814: 'Twas the Night Before (Krampus) Christmas
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music for the season, New Sounds-style, with lesser-known traditional carols, as well as unexpected arrangements of overplayed classics.

episodesByNumber.title: #3815: John Schaefer's Top 10 for 2015
episodesByNumber.tease: In a not-so-shocking break with tradition, John Schaefer reveals his "Best Of 2015" list, before 2015 actually ends, but long after most best-of lists have gone to print or air.

episodesByNumber.title: #3816: New Releases, December 2015 Edition
episodesByNumber.tease: Specially aged for the holidays, hear some December 2015 new releases. Sample a cross-cultural work by Ablaye Cissoko  &  Constantinople Ensemble, the film score to The Revenant,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3817: With Jeremy Flower, 'The Real Me'
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, multi-instrumentalist and composer Jeremy Flower presents his song cycle for large chamber ensemble "The Real Me."

episodesByNumber.title: #3818: Music from the Folk Tradition
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear works rooted in the folk tradition on this New Sounds program from the Unthanks, the Baird Sisters, Aoife O'Donovan, and the group called United Bible Studies.

episodesByNumber.title: #3819: David Bowie, A Tribute
episodesByNumber.tease: To mark the 5th anniversary of David Bowie's death, host John Schaefer offers an hour of music by Bowie, for Bowie, or variations on themes by Bowie.

episodesByNumber.title: #3820: Orbiting Daniel Wohl’s 'Holographic'
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music by French-born Brooklyn-based composer Daniel Wohl, from his latest release, "Holographic," along with music by Caroline Shaw and Olga Bell.

episodesByNumber.title: #3821: With Donald Nally, Director of The Crossing
episodesByNumber.tease: Donald Nally, Director of Philadelphia choir The Crossing, joins John to present portions of "The Fifth Century," a work written by Gavin Bryars for the choir  &  the PRISM Sax Quartet.

episodesByNumber.title: #3822: Non-Rock Music for Rock Instruments
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to composed pieces which use electric guitars and basses and/or drums, by Noveller (Sarah Lipstate), English composer Joby Talbot, Steve Reich, the Japanese band, Mono and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3823: Living Opera and Sound Design, with Tom Hamilton
episodesByNumber.tease: Visit with electronic composer and sound designer Tom Hamilton, who collaborated with the late Robert Ashley, including on Ashley's opera-novel, "Quicksand."

episodesByNumber.title: #3824: New Releases, January 2016 Edition
episodesByNumber.tease: It's the most wonderful time of the month, it's the new releases show, featuring brand-new music from multi-instrumentalist/producer/composer and violinist Emily Wells  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3825: With Emily Wells
episodesByNumber.tease: Violinist, vocalist, looper, composer and producer Emily Wells presents and performs songs from her record, "Promise," with John Schaefer.

episodesByNumber.title: #3826: Music With Found Voices
episodesByNumber.tease: For this episode, hear works that take the human voice as a starting point from Steve Reich, Julia Wolfe, Ingram Marshall, and Florent Ghys.

episodesByNumber.title: #3827: Chamber Rock and Jazz
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, listen to a smorgasbord of new music: chamber rock, chamber jazz, and post-rock from the seminal post-rock band Rachel's to the piano trio called Gogo Penguin.

episodesByNumber.title: #3828: More Music for Pictures at an Exhibition
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to works inspired by some of the great painters of the 20th Century: Kandinsky, Schiele  &  Miró, in music by Brooklyn Rider, the group Rachel's  &  drummer/composer Bobby Previte.

episodesByNumber.title: #3829: Ted Hearne's "The Source"
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, composer Ted Hearne joins John Schaefer to present "The Source," an oratorio based the story of U.S. Army Private Manning and drawn from primary sources.

episodesByNumber.title: #3830: Big Bands and Bands That Just Sound Big
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music featuring larger ensembles, or that which might have a big band sound, from Debo Band, Eco-Music Big Band, music by Laura Jurd,  &  something from Scottish drummer Corrie Dick.

episodesByNumber.title: #3831: With Third Coast Percussion
episodesByNumber.tease: Members of Chicago-based quartet Third Coast Percussion present a major piece for percussion by Irish composer Donnacha Dennehy, along with works by Steve Reich.

episodesByNumber.title: #3832: East, Central, and West Asian-inflected Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music that draws on traditions from East, West, and Central Asia -  from the likes of Jaimeo Brown Transcendence, the Gurdjieff Ensemble, Betty Olivero,  &  Herbie Mann.

episodesByNumber.title: #3833: New Sounds Live: Rachel Grimes and Longleash
episodesByNumber.tease: From New Sounds Live, hear music from the piano trio Longleash together with pianist/composer Rachel Grimes, a member of the post-rock group Rachel's in "Music for Egon Schiele."

episodesByNumber.title: #3834: New Music from / About Iceland
episodesByNumber.tease: For this episode, hear new music from Iceland by way of Ireland, Australia, and New York as well as music made about an imaginary Iceland from Linda Buckley, Nico Muhly, and Ben Frost.

episodesByNumber.title: #3835: With Thomas Bartlett of The Gloaming
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, The Gloaming's Thomas Bartlett, aka Doveman, presents selections from the Irish-American supergroup's spellbinding second album, The Gloaming 2  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3836: New Releases, February 2016 (Leap Day Edition)
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music from Cuban pianist/composer Alfredo Rodriguez, French trumpeter Ibrahim Maalouf, electro-chamber music by George Hurd, Afro-Columbian dance-grooves from Sidestepper  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3837: Bang on a Can PCF Concert 2016
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear four world-premiere works from the 2016 Bang on a Can People's Commissioning Fund Concert, played by the Bang on a Can All-Stars, part of the Ecstatic Music Festival at Merkin Hall.

episodesByNumber.title: #3838: New Music With Trumpet
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to new music with trumpet including music from the Paris-based trumpeter Ibrahim Maalouf, Iraqi-American trumpeter Amir Elsaffar, Ben Neill's mutanttrumpet, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3839: The Sound of Abstraction
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to works that embrace the elusive abstract reality of ideas. Hear works from harpist Mary Lattimore, violinist Sarah Neufeld, Nathan Davis, Anna Thorvaldsdottir  &  George Hurd.
tags: young peoples chorus of new york city

episodesByNumber.title: #3840: Music From 1 to 12 Strings (Guitars, Mostly)
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear fingerstyle guitar from William Tyler (electric) and from Glenn Jones (acoustic), music from The Baird Sisters, Guy Buttery with Derek Gripper,  &  music by the late Nana Vasconcelos.

episodesByNumber.title: #3841: With Dan Trueman & Rebecca Lazier
episodesByNumber.tease: Composer/fiddle player/Princeton University professor Dan Trueman joins New York-based choreographer Rebecca Lazier to present the collaborative multimedia work, There Might Be Others.

episodesByNumber.title: #3842: Music Inspired by NASA and Space
episodesByNumber.tease: Explore the sounds beyond our home planet in music inspired by NASA, the race for space, and overcoming fears in works by Quindar, Laurie Anderson,  &  Public Service Broadcasting.

episodesByNumber.title: #3843: Stumbling through Gaelic: Music Based on Irish Song
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to an hour of songs with Gaelic titles, from the Irish folk tradition in contemporary arrangements, as well as composed pieces by Kate Moore, Donnacha Dennehy, and David Flynn.

episodesByNumber.title: #3844: Under the Influence of Louis Andriessen
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music by Dutch composer, pianist, and teacher Louis Andriessen, and those under his influence - like Julia Wolfe, Missy Mazzoli, Nathan Michel, and the late Steve Martland.

episodesByNumber.title: #3845: Sam Amidon and Nico Muhly
episodesByNumber.tease: Composer, arranger, and co-founder of the Bedroom Community record label Nico Muhly, and Vermont-born singer/fiddler/banjoist/guitarist Sam Amidon join John Schaefer in the studio.

episodesByNumber.title: #3846: Chamber Music, of a Sort
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, hear chamber music of a sort from the collaborative quartet Collectress, in the vein of Penguin Café Orchestra, music from Penguin Café, Max Richter, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3847: New Sounds Live - The Trimbin Band
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear film scores by the Trimbin Band—Nick Hallett, Mikael Jorgensen, James Merle Thomas, William Tyler—to filmic excerpts from Los Angeles-based filmmaker  &  folk musician Fred Engelberg.

episodesByNumber.title: #3848: New Releases, March 2016
episodesByNumber.tease: New releases, including forthcoming records by Leyla McCalla, Colin Stetson, and Brian Eno, along with new cosmic duo music by Vijay Iyer  &  Wadada Leo Smith, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3849: A New Breed of Art-Rock
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music by the new breed of art-rock bands, who aren't concerned with pop song form, and draw from jazz, minimalism, chamber music, Afrobeat,  &  anything else that suits them.

episodesByNumber.title: #3850: Finding Their Roots
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music exploring musical and cultural roots by Syrian clarinetist Kinan Azmeh  &  the Silk Road Ensemble, from New Orleans-based singer/cellist Leyla McCalla,  &  Yemeni sisters, A-wa.

episodesByNumber.title: #3851: Marking Ravi Shankar's Birthday
episodesByNumber.tease: To celebrate the birthday of the late sitar master Ravi Shankar, listen to a tribute from his daughter Anoushka Shankar, along with rare archival performances  &  collaborations.

episodesByNumber.title: #3852: Kronos Quartet's 50 for the Future
episodesByNumber.tease: Kronos Quartet's founding violinist David Harrington shares new works written for and recorded by Kronos Quartet, but ultimately not intended for them - part of Fifty for the Future.

episodesByNumber.title: #3853: Under the Chamber Music Umbrella
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear chamber music on this New Sounds from a choir of cellos performed by Ashley Bathgate, the choir of voices in Tenebrae, a choir of strings in the Tallin Chamber Orchestra,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3854: Funky Romania
episodesByNumber.tease: Celebrate the sounds of Romanian music on this New Sounds, with Romanian bands  - like Fanfare Ciocarlia- and bands from France, Ireland, Spain,  &  New York who look to music of Romania.

episodesByNumber.title: #3855: Choral & Vocal Works From Abroad
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to an hour of choral and vocal works from abroad, with music performed by the Estonian Philharmonic Chamber Choir, a setting of an Icelandic psalm by Anna Thorvaldsdottir,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3856: New Releases, April 2016
episodesByNumber.tease: New music from flamenco guitarist Pedro Soler  &  his son, "cross-country" cellist Gaspar Claus, cellist Joan Jeanrenaud, Nashville-based guitarist William Tyler,  &  Nik Bärtsch's Mobile.

episodesByNumber.title: #3857: New "Chamber Orchestras"
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, listen to new music for chamber orchestra and mixed ensembles of varying size, featuring Colin Stetson's "Sorrow", Dal Niente  &  Deerhoof,  &  harpist Valérie Milot.

episodesByNumber.title: #3858: Collaborative Works
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear collaborative works, featuring music by Kaki King with ETHEL, a work by Chris Cerrone with Eighth Blackbird, and the Berlin Guitar Ensemble with producer 1605munro.

episodesByNumber.title: #3859: Cross-Cultural Collaborations
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music from Norwegian pianist Tord Gustavsen, German-Afghan vocalist Simin Tander, and drummer Jarle Vespestad, plus Pakistani-Brooklyn group Sandaraa,  &  Congolese-Irish music.

episodesByNumber.title: #3860: Layers & Electronics
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music with multiple layers, and/or music created with electronics for this New Sounds from Nik Bärtsch's Mobile, Kate Moore  &  Ashley Bathgate, Maya Beiser  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3861: Music Inspired by the Colorado River and Grand Canyon
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music inspired by or written in the Grand Canyon or on the Colorado River for this New Sounds, including selections from the eco-documentary, "The Colorado," and other works.

episodesByNumber.title: #3862: Onze Danses and Beyond
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear selections from the newly-reissued Onze danses pour combattre la migraine, from Aksak Maboul. Plus, musical projects by Aksak band members Mark Hollander  &  Vincent Kenis,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3863: With Singer/Composer Alev Lenz
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear electroacoustic works by London-based Alev Lenz, and more music that limns the European classical  &  Western pop music divide. Plus, music by Kaitlyn Aurelia Smith  &  Anna Meredith.

episodesByNumber.title: #3864: The Tuvan Connection
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear some intersections of western and Tuvan folk music on this New Sounds, from New York-based Hazmat Modine, the Tuvan groups Huun Huur Tu, Yat-Kha, Alash, bluesman Paul Pena,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3865: The Other Classical Musics, With Michael Church
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music around the world from some of the 15 classical music traditions covered in Michael Church's book, The Other Classical Musics.

episodesByNumber.title: #3866: Time and/or Site-Specific Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear new vocal works, specific to a place, or even a time, on this New Sounds, from Lesley Flanigan, Julia Wolfe, Finnegan Shanahan, and Lewis Pesacov.

episodesByNumber.title: #3867: May 2016 New Releases
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear new releases from May, including music from string quartet ETHEL  &  Native American flutist Robert Mirabal, as well as Welsh-language sextet 9Bach  &  layers of Julianna Barwick.

episodesByNumber.title: #3868: Womens' Voices and Electronics
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, listen to the combination of human voice and electronics in computer-based music by Roger Doyle, Leila Adu, Anna Meredith,  &  Jacob Cooper.

episodesByNumber.title: #3869: The Goat as Musical Hero
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to a program celebrating the goat, with works about goats, and works featuring instruments made from parts of the goat, all kick-started by the band Ten Strings and a Goat Skin.
tags: ten strings and a goat skin

episodesByNumber.title: #3870: New York Guitar Festival at the Greene Space, part 1 of 2
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear world premiere works by guitar wizards, recorded at the Greene Space from the 2016 New York Guitar Festival, featuring the artistry of Kaki King, Glenn Jones,  &  Derek Gripper.

episodesByNumber.title: #3871: New York Guitar Festival at the Greene Space, part 2 of 2
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear world premiere works from the 2016 New York Guitar Festival Event recorded at the Greene Space, featuring the artistry of Rez Abbasi, Kaki King, Glenn Jones,  &  Derek Gripper.

episodesByNumber.title: #3872: An Electroacoustic Affair
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to the combination of electronic music and voice, traditional folk instruments, and/or chamber music instruments with works by Sarathy Korwar, Eleonore Oppenheim,  &  Jambinai.

episodesByNumber.title: #3873 Music by Bryars, The Crossing, & PRISM Quartet
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to portions of Gavin Bryars' new piece, "The Fifth Century,"  &  his work "New York." Also, hear magnetic choral music from The Crossing  &  Philadelphia-based PRISM Quartet,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3874: Extensions of the Guitar
episodesByNumber.tease: Explore extensions of the guitar through the use of electronics, innovative guitar-work, and music for harp guitar by Calum Graham, Kaki King, Andre LaFosse,  &  Dominic Frasca.

episodesByNumber.title: #3875: Music from Southern Italy & Sardinia
episodesByNumber.tease: Take a voyage to Southern Italy and the island of Sardinia, both regions possessed of distinct musical character. Hear examples of tarantellas, the male voices of cantu a tenore,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3876: New Releases, June 2016
episodesByNumber.tease: It's already past the end of the month,  &  time to hear choral work from Tim Hecker, a new project from legendary Afrobeat drummer Tony Allen, new music from cellist Maya Beiser,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3877: Appalachian Echoes
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to Appalachian-leaning minimalism from Arnold Dreyblatt and Megafaun, along with vocal work from Moira Smiley  &  VOCO, music from one of Yo-Yo Ma's Appalachian projects,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3878: Music for Jaw Harp
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, hear the jaw harp in music from Kazakhstan to the Appalachians, from Estonia to China, with music from Kepa Junkera  &  Sorginak, Wang Li  &  Wu Wei, and Rashanim.

episodesByNumber.title: #3879: Cistern  Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music from the late Pauline Oliveros  &  Jherek Bischoff, among others, recorded in  &  inspired by a massive cistern under the now-decommissioned Fort Worden in Port Townsend, WA.

episodesByNumber.title: #3880: Americana Chamber Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to chamber music packed with strong Americana flavors with works from ETHEL  &  flutist Robert Mirabal, violist/composer Jessica Meyer, and guitarist/composer Bill Frisell.

episodesByNumber.title: #3881: Music for Weddings and Funerals
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to some wedding and funeral music the world over – from Benin, Macedonia, Romania, Syria, and Brooklyn. Plus Balkan brass from Goran Bregović  &  the Wedding and Funeral Orchestra.

episodesByNumber.title: #3882: New Music from Montréal
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music made by Montréal-based composers/musicians such as organist/composer Kara-Lis Coverdale, the chamber band Esmerine, GY!BE,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3883: On the Road
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, hear works written on the road by Mary Lattimore, George Hurd and Clint Needham. Plus, music from the soundtrack to the film adaptation of "The Road"  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3884: New Releases, July 2016
episodesByNumber.tease: It's new music from July 2016, a bit late - with works by Christopher Tignor, Beaunoise, Stein Urheim  &  more. Plus, works by Philip Glass arranged and performed by Anton Batagov.

episodesByNumber.title: #3885: Ghost Songs
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music about ghosts for this New Sounds show - from a love poem sung in Gaelic to mostly instrumental music from Oregon-based Ash Black Bufflo, music by Hauschka,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3886: West African Strings
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear traditional string instruments of Western Africa, like the kora, ngoni,  &  the guitar (now traditional), with music by Seckou Keita, Djelimady Tounkara,  &  Noura Mint Seymali.

episodesByNumber.title: #3887: The Dark Side of British Folk
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear darker folk songs from the British Isles including music by the Unthanks, Lau, Alasdair Roberts  &  Mairi Morrison, and singer/writer/concertina player Emily Portman.

episodesByNumber.title: #3888: New Music from Brazil
episodesByNumber.tease: From samba bands to experimental sounds, along with distinguished icons like Elza Soares and the legendary Caetano Veloso, hear new music from Brazil.

episodesByNumber.title: #3889: With Lukas Ligeti
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music from percussionist and composer Lukas Ligeti. Hear influences of West African rhythms  &  architecture in his composed works  &  improvisations.

episodesByNumber.title: #3890: Echoes of Crafty Guitar
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear guitar re-imagined for harp, happiness re-imagined by instruments, and kitchens of the utmost distinction.

episodesByNumber.title: #3891: Electronic Music Looking Back
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear electronic music made with synthesizers by Kaitlyn Aurelia Smith, Floating Points (aka Sam Shepherd), the Belgian band Aksak Maboul,  &  Wendy Carlos.

episodesByNumber.title: #3892: Percussion Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music for percussion on this New Sounds from drummer Kid Millions, aka John Colpitts, plus music from TIGUE  &  Man Forever (also Colpitts) and works by Marc Mellits  &  Paul Lansky.

episodesByNumber.title: #3893: With Guitarist Guy Buttery
episodesByNumber.tease: South African guitarist Guy Buttery visits the studio to perform virtuosic feats of bending, tapping, picking, harmonics, and other techniques and textures yet to be named for guitar.

episodesByNumber.title: #3894: With Christopher Tignor
episodesByNumber.tease: Christopher Tignor plays works from Along A Vanishing Plane with violin, tuning forks  &  string electromagnetics, kick drum, and a laptop using sound-altering software that he designed.

episodesByNumber.title: #3895: New Releases, August 2016
episodesByNumber.tease: John Schaefer presents new releases for the month of August, including works from the Neil Cowley Trio, the FatCat imprint 130701, music from the "Swiss Army Man" soundtrack, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3896: New Chamber Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to new chamber music plus electronics in works by Dublin-based composer Benedict Schlepper-Connolly, American composer Marti Epstein, and the Icelandic composer Ólafur Arnalds.

episodesByNumber.title: #3897: Music Rooted in the Near East and North Africa,
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, explore music with roots in both the west and the Near East and North Africa from Amina Alaoui, Basel Rajoub, and Benjamim Taubkin, among others.

episodesByNumber.title: #3898: Musical Mourning
episodesByNumber.tease: The lament as something that you can perform has been the genesis for many works over the years. Hear music of mourning from Ingram Marshall, Eleni Karaindrou, Tiange Zhou, and others.

episodesByNumber.title: #3899: Covers – the Deep Cuts, New Sounds-Style
episodesByNumber.tease: From a Georgian folk song to covers of Duke Ellington's Far East Suite and an R. Kelly song, it's all here: jazz, rock, folk music of east  &  west, plus Qawwali music, and Kraftwerk.

episodesByNumber.title: #3900: New Music With Flutes
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear works for multiple flutes including the first of Steve Reich's "Counterpoint" pieces, along with flutes from Bolivia, and the traditional flutes of Japan: shakuhachi  &  shinobue.

episodesByNumber.title: #3901: Music for the Days of the Week
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music for each of the seven days of the week, from Stockhausen to Florent Ghys's chamber band Bonjour, with groove jazz  &  Mediterranean traditional music from Thrace along the way.

episodesByNumber.title: #3902: A Tribute to Erik Satie
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to an hour of musical tributes to the French composer, eccentric,  &  proto-minimalist Erik Satie (1866-1925) from Daniel Lanois on pedal steel, Guy Klucevsek on accordion  &  others.

episodesByNumber.title: #3903: Songs of St. Kilda
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear the forgotten songs of St. Kilda, along with re-imagined poems and songs inspired by these remote islands, nearly 100 miles off the coast of Scotland.

episodesByNumber.title: #3904: With Darcy James Argue
episodesByNumber.tease: Composer, bandleader, and ringleader Darcy James Argue visits the studio to introduce selections from his latest record, Real Enemies, a 13-chapter work exploring conspiracy theories.

episodesByNumber.title: #3905: Getting Back to Their Roots Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Composers examine their musical roots, from the South Carolina Sea Islands, to coal mines of central Pennsylvania, from Ireland and the Great Famine of the 19th Century, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3906: New Releases, September 2016
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear new music for September in releases by Beninese Orchestre Poly-Rythmo, Alsarah and the Nubatones, Montreal-based saxophonist/composer Jason Sharp,  &  bassist/composer Daniel Foose.

episodesByNumber.title: #3907: Steve Reich, a Musical Tribute on His Birthday
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to the wide-ranging influence of composer Steve Reich in electronica, music by the late Gyorgi Ligeti, chamber dub,  &  an arrangement of Sondheim. Today is Reich's 80th birthday.

episodesByNumber.title: #3908: With Baird Hersey (Prana) & Garry Kvistad (NEXUS Percussion)
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music from Baird Hersey and the harmonic singing group Prana together with the Toronto-based percussion group Nexus led by Garry Kvistad for this New Sounds.

episodesByNumber.title: #3909: Unconventional Solos (and a Duo)
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear unbelievable solos, like music for saxophone by Colin Stetson, acrobatic feats on violin by Sarah Neufeld, zither from Laraaji, cello soundscapes by way of Iceland,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3910: With Pete M. Wyer and Shigeru Miyagawa
episodesByNumber.tease: Composer Pete M. Wyer  &  MIT professor Shigeru Miyagawa visit the studio, in advance of Wyer's New Sounds Live commission, "Song of the Human," a work for both birdsong and human voices.

episodesByNumber.title: #3911: Echoes of Africa
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear "Echoes of Africa," featuring Vernon Reid's "Artificial Afrika," plus rearrangements of work/field songs from Jaimeo Brown, Linda Tillery  &  the Cultural Heritage Choir,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3912: With Zakir Hussain & Niladri Kumar
episodesByNumber.tease: "Indian music does not stop and start with Ravi Shankar," says tabla master Zakir Hussain, who, along with young sitar virtuoso, Niladri Kumar, performs in our studio.

episodesByNumber.title: #3913: New Sounds Live at Brookfield Place, 2016
episodesByNumber.tease: From the New Sounds Live Concert Series, hear music performed within Pete M. Wyer's sound installation, by Sarah Neufeld/Colin Stetson, by Vernon Reid and Laraaji,  &  The Crossing choir.

episodesByNumber.title: #3914: With Abigail Washburn & Wu Fei
episodesByNumber.tease: Beijing-born, Nashville-based composer  &  guzheng performer Wu Fei joins banjo player/songwriter Abigail Washburn for a commingling of Chinese  &  Appalachian folk music in our studio.

episodesByNumber.title: #3915: Music with Irish or Scottish Roots
episodesByNumber.tease: There's music with roots in Irish or Scottish singing: Irish fiddler Martin Hayes and American guitarist Dennis Cahill - in a quartet and as The Gloaming - and music from singer Peia.

episodesByNumber.title: #3916: New Sounds Live: Pete M. Wyer's 'Song of the Human'
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear the world premiere of Pete M. Wyer's New Sounds Live commission, "Song of the Human," a work for both birdsong and human voices, featuring Philadelphia-based choir, The Crossing.

episodesByNumber.title: #3917: New Releases, October 2016
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear new music from Norwegian guitarist Geir Sundstøl, music for tunable Brazilian berimbau, a song by Denmark-based Gambian griot Dawda Jobarteh,  &  new work from Tanya Tagaq.

episodesByNumber.title: #3918: With Roger Goula
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear post-classical electronica by Spanish-born, London-based composer, songwriter, and multi-instrumentalist Roger Goula, recorded on location.

episodesByNumber.title: #3919: With Composer Mamoru Fujieda
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, hear works both old and new with a ritual aspect - including the sounds of fermenting shochu - by Japanese post-minimal composer Mamoru Fujieda.

episodesByNumber.title: #3920: 'Heresy' by Roger Doyle
episodesByNumber.tease: From Dublin, hear Irishman Roger Doyle present portions of his new opera Heresy, based on the life and death of Giordano Bruno, the 16th century Dominican friar and martyr for science.

episodesByNumber.title: #3921: World/Chamber Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear instruments of the Indonesian court meeting a string quartet, western music for gamelan featuring an Irish dancer, and Ethiopian music for string quartet.

episodesByNumber.title: #3922: A Sampling of New Sounds Live 2016 Concerts
episodesByNumber.tease: Sample music from New Sounds Live 2016, recorded live at Brookfield Place, with music from Sarah Neufeld  &  Colin Stetson (of Arcade Fire), Vernon Reid  &  Laraaji,  &  The Crossing Choir.

episodesByNumber.title: #3923: November 2016 New Releases & A Gun Show
episodesByNumber.tease: Preview So Percussion's A Gun Show  &  hear the best new music to have crossed John Schaefer's desk/inbox/earholes, with Sinikka Langeland's kantele-jazz, Flamingods' folkadelica,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3924: From the Huddersfield, UK Contemporary Music Festival
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, hear some of the music recorded on location at the 39th annual Huddersfield Contemporary Music Festival in Northern England.

episodesByNumber.title: #3925: Music From Eastern Europe
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, hear music by women from Eastern Europe, featuring music from Poland, Ukraine, Serbia, and the Czech Republic, plus music from the Bulgarian Women's Chorus.

episodesByNumber.title: #3926: Extending the Art Song Tradition
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to vocal pieces on this edition of New Sounds, which definitely extend the idea of the art song, featuring music from The Living Earth Show, and Nico Muhly, among others.

episodesByNumber.title: #3927: Classical Instruments, Contemporary Sounds
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music that begins with classical instruments, like the string quartet, piano, or an orchestra, but which is then augmented, enhanced by electronics, percussion, and/or preparation.

episodesByNumber.title: #3928: With Guitarist Shane Parish
episodesByNumber.tease: Guitarist Shane Parish, of the instrumental prog-punk band Ahleuchatistas, plays music from his solo record of "weird old Americana" live in the studio on acoustic and prepared guitar.

episodesByNumber.title: #3929: With Dublin Guitar Quartet's Brian Bolger & Composer Michael Gordon
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear the Dublin Guitar Quartet go electric for Bang on a Can Co-Founder Michael Gordon's work, "Amplified," and then acoustic for other works.

episodesByNumber.title: #3930: Modern Cumbia and The Chicha Renaissance
episodesByNumber.tease: Modern takes on cumbia and Chicha style with music from Austin-based Money Chicha, Arizona-based Orkesta Mendoza, Argentinian Chancha Via Circuito, Brooklyn-based Chicha Libre,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3931: Claudia Molitor With Partch Instruments
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to microtonally-oriented music by English-German composer Claudia Molitor written for newly built Harry Partch Instruments, live from Huddersfield Contemporary Music Festival.

episodesByNumber.title: #3932: New Releases, December 2016 Edition
episodesByNumber.tease: Specially aged for the holidays, it's the December 2016 new releases program!

episodesByNumber.title: #3933: Music For An Experience
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music inspired by a story, an image, or a theatrical experience, including selections from the dance score to "The Painted Bird" by Christian Frederickson and Ryan Rumery.

episodesByNumber.title: #3934: Works by Bang On A Can PCF Alumni
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music from composers who have been commissioned by Bang on a Can to write music for the Bang on a Can All-Stars for this New Sounds, including Nico Muhly, Anna Clyne,  &  others.

episodesByNumber.title: #3935: A World Tour of Beatboxing
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, hear music from Brazil, Finland, Ireland, Iraq, Romania meets Appalachia, all with a rhythmic bed of beatboxing.

episodesByNumber.title: #3936: With Anna Thorvaldsdottir
episodesByNumber.tease: The Icelandic composer Anna Thorvaldsdottir joins John Schaefer for this New Sounds. Listen to a cross section of her works, and hear her response to "Is there something about Iceland?"

episodesByNumber.title: #3937: John Schaefer's Top Ten for 2016
episodesByNumber.tease: John Schaefer reveals his very tardy Top Ten Of 2016 list. Highlights include a plea for the planet, rearrangements of work songs, kora music adapted for guitar,  &  an Icelandic opus.

episodesByNumber.title: #3938: Meredith Monk, On Behalf of Nature, In-Studio
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear an hour of music by vocalist/composer/choreographer Meredith Monk, including portions of her latest record, "On Behalf of Nature," in the studio.

episodesByNumber.title: #3939: New York New Music Ensembles
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to three generations of New York-based new music ensembles from the NOW Ensemble to yMusic, to the Bang on a Can All-Stars, and the Philip Glass Ensemble.

episodesByNumber.title: #3940: Music Inspired by the Natural World
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to works inspired by the natural world, i.e. birds  &  insects to larger scale works about oceans. Plus things that are too tiny or too cosmic to see, like dark matter and viruses.
tags: a winged victory for the sullen

episodesByNumber.title: #3941: Northern Fiddles
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to Northern fiddles for this New Sounds, a hybrid of traditional Irish and Nordic folk music, which blends these fiddles with marimba, trumpet, electronics, sax, and concertina.

episodesByNumber.title: #3942: New Releases, January 2017
episodesByNumber.tease: It's the end of the month, which is the time for sharing the latest releases that have come across John Schaefer's desk and into the New Sounds inbox.

episodesByNumber.title: #3943: The Collaborative Side of Philip Glass
episodesByNumber.tease: Celebrate his 80th birthday of Philip Glass with an hour of music highlighting the collaborative side of Philip Glass.

episodesByNumber.title: #3944: Immigrant Songs
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music from The Nile Project, The Silk Road Ensemble, and Montreal-based ensemble Constantinople - all cross-cultural musical collaborations among artists from very diverse places.

episodesByNumber.title: #3945: The Subtle Side of Percussion
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear softer music featuring percussion from Brisbane's Clocked Out, the Danish quartet We Like We, So Percussion, The Living Earth Show, a work by Gavin Bryars, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3946: Some Recent World Music,
episodesByNumber.tease: Sample music from Finland by kantele artist Pauliina Syrjälä, along with music from Mali by Awa Poulo, and music from Poland. Plus music from Burkina Faso, Bosnia, and The Nile Project.

episodesByNumber.title: #3947: English Folk - Traditional Tales of Love & Woe
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear tales of love gone wrong, songs about the sea  &  other old folk songs in interesting, sometimes multicultural arrangements by The Imagined Village, Sheila Chandra  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3948: Responses to Early Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to works that look back to early music; some inspired by the 16th-century murderer-prince Carlo Gesualdo, and others as responses to the 17th-century Baroque composer Buxtehude.

episodesByNumber.title: #3949: Accumulating Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music made by the process of accumulating layers of sound for this New Sounds from Grant Cutler, Daniel Lentz, Robert Fripp, and Julianna Barwick.

episodesByNumber.title: #3950: Keyboard Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music involving keyboards – all kinds, from jazz-ish organ of Medeski, Martin  &  Wood  &  The Necks, to toy piano of Phyllis Chen and the unadorned piano of Craig Taborn

episodesByNumber.title: #3951: With Ralph Towner
episodesByNumber.tease: Guitarist, pianist,  &  composer Ralph Towner who is also a co-founder of the group Oregon, joins us in the studio for live guitar-artistry for this New Sounds.

episodesByNumber.title: #3952: Acoustic Music From Electronic Composers
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music played by "real" instruments which reflects a composer's familiarity with electronic instruments, in works by Son Lux and yMusic, Sarah Kirkland Snider, and Steve Reich.

episodesByNumber.title: #3953: Music Inspired by North Africa
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear some recent releases that look to North Africa; to a place between Tunisia  &  Algeria, as far east as Ethiopia,  &  the sounds of traditional Moroccan Gnawa trance rhythms.

episodesByNumber.title: #3954: Music for Bowed Strings and Voices
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to works all built around sounds of strings with and without voices: Nordic Affect plays music by Úlfur Hansson, hear music by Jane Antonia Cornish, Arvo Pärt, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3955: Unusually Constructed Chamber Ensembles
episodesByNumber.tease: From a Michigan-based reed quintet to a European foursome of cello, piano, soprano sax, and accordion, to a string quartet with a banjo player, hear unusually constructed chamber groups.

episodesByNumber.title: #3956: New Sounds Live at Ecstatic Music 2017 - NOW Ensemble and San Fermin
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear newly-composed epic chamber-pop and orchestrated songs in music by NOW Ensemble and the band San Fermin, from the Ecstatic Music Festival 2017 recorded live at Merkin Hall.

episodesByNumber.title: #3957: Acoustic & Sampled Indie Classical
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear sample-heavy music from Nick Zammuto  &  Paul de Jong, as The Books, along with related music from Roomful of Teeth, NOW Ensemble, Nick Zammuto with Jason Treuting, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3958: The Afro-Cuban Connection
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music with an Afro-Cuban connection, including music by Cuban pianist Omar Sosa and Senegalese kora master, Sekou Keita, from the stunning release, "Transparent Water."

episodesByNumber.title: #3959: Live from Winnipeg New Music Festival 2017, Part I
episodesByNumber.tease: From the 2017 edition of the annual Winnigpeg New Music Festival, hear recordings of performances by Jessica Moss, William Basinski, and Lubomyr Melnyk.

episodesByNumber.title: #3960: We've Got Rhythms
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to rhythmic music, in a work from the Jasper String Quartet, a prepared piano piece by Kelly Moran, and a vocal duet from Meredith Monk and Robert Een.

episodesByNumber.title: #3961: Roomful of Teeth & Nick Zammuto from New Sounds Live/Ecstatic Music Festival 2017
episodesByNumber.tease: From the 2017 Ecstatic Music Festival at Merkin Hall, listen to vocal-driven adventures via Roomful of Teeth, in collaboration with composer Nick Zammuto, and new work by Caroline Shaw.

episodesByNumber.title: #3962: Musical Stillness
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear musical stillness, in new music from Icelandic composer/violinist Maria Huld Markan Sigfusdottir (of amiina)  &  in music by Canadian-born composer composer/pianist John Kameel Farah.

episodesByNumber.title: #3963: Steve Reich's 80th Birthday Season
episodesByNumber.tease: Steve Reich, a composer whose influence ranges across generations, visits the studio, marking the celebration of his 80th birthday season.

episodesByNumber.title: #3964: A Touch of Jazz
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music which enters the realm of jazz, but admits other sounds from other parts of the world by Ingrid  &  Christine Jensen, Serbian quartet EYOT,  &  Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah.

episodesByNumber.title: #3965: Music Based on Buddhist Prayer
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music centered on Buddhist prayer from Russian pianist/composer Anton Batagov, together with Tibetan devotional singer Yungchen Lhamo,  &  as part of a new work, "The One Thus Gone."

episodesByNumber.title: #3966: All About Drones
episodesByNumber.tease: This edition of New Sounds is all about drones, including music from Montreal-based Saltland, New York composer Nico Muhly, Estonian vocalist/violinist Maarja Nuut,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3967: New Releases, March 2017
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear the collective known as Les Amazones d'Afrique - great women musicians from Benin, Gabon, Mali,  &  Nigeria. Also, chamber jazz by Daniel Herskedal  &  Tuareg rockenroll by Tamikrest.

episodesByNumber.title: #3968: Piano-Based New Music
episodesByNumber.tease: From prepared piano, bowed piano, to player piano, listen to new music by Kelly Moran, Ólafur Arnalds, Tigran Hamasyan, and Polish composer Jakub Ciupinski for pianist Vicky Chow.

episodesByNumber.title: #3969: Post-Rock & Post-Classical Works
episodesByNumber.tease: From the cinematic, experimental soundscapes of one-woman band Noveller to the Japanese band Mono's stately slow-build instrumentals, hear music with the possible label of "post-rock."

episodesByNumber.title: #3970: With Matthew Patton
episodesByNumber.tease: Canadian composer Matthew Patton just released a hauntingly emotive requiem, The Infected Mass, under the name Those Who Walk Away. Host John Schafefer caught up with Patton in Winnipeg.

episodesByNumber.title: #3971: Beyond the Piano Trio
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear new music for the combination of piano, bass and drums, and beyond - featuring new music from the trio Bearthoven, Tyondai Braxton for Yarn/Wire, and Omar Sosa  &  Seckou Keita.

episodesByNumber.title: #3972: New Sounds Live/Ecstatic Music Festival -Bang on a Can PCF 2017
episodesByNumber.tease: From the New Sounds Live Concerts at Merkin Hall, in partnership with the Ecstatic Music Festival, hear music from the 2017 Bang on a Can People's Commissioning Fund Concert.

episodesByNumber.title: #3973: Inspired by Tarkovsky
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music inspired by or taken from Andrei Tarkovsky films by his composer Edward Artemiev, an alternate score by Ben Frost and Daníel Bjarnason, and an homage by Toru Takemitsu.

episodesByNumber.title: #3974: The Dark Side of Folk Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear the weird and the dark side of folk music, from the Canadian North  &  Finland, from the Moravian folk tradition, and Balkan-influenced renaissance dance music from Paris/Brussels.

episodesByNumber.title: #3975: African Big Bands
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music from great African big bands, like Fela Kuti  &  Africa 70, Franco  &  Le TPOK jazz, and the Ethiojazz of Mulatu Astatke, representing Nigeria, Congo, and Ethiopia, respectively.

episodesByNumber.title: #3976: Recent Ambient and Atmospheric Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music by Ryuichi Sakamoto, from "Async," new Arabic traditional music by Duo Sabîl, atmospheric chamber music by Irish composer and guitarist Benjamin Dwyer, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3977: New Music From Estonia
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music by Estonian composers Arvo Pärt and Mirjam Tally, as well as music from the late Estonian composer Veljo Tormis. Plus, listen to works by Urmas Sisask  &  Erkki-Sven Tüür.

episodesByNumber.title: #3978: With Arthur Jeffes, of The Penguin Cafe
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear a conversation with English composer Arthur Jeffes, who leads the band Penguin Café. Their 2017 album 'The Imperfect Sea', is a collection of dance music made on real instruments.

episodesByNumber.title: #3979: East Meets West - Asian-Inflected Cross-Cultural Collaborations
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear songs that combine east  &  west; music that draws from sounds of Azerbaijan, Bahrain, Afghanistan, India, Pakistan  &  the west. Listen to works by Yazz Ahmed, Najma, Ya Tosiba  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3980: Bass-Based Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to bass-based music for this edition of New Sounds, with works from Italian bass player Silvia Bolognesi (Hear In Now), Florent Ghys, the late Charlie Haden,  &  Edgar Meyer.

episodesByNumber.title: #3981: Bruce Odland & Rinde Eckert in The TANK
episodesByNumber.tease: Composer Bruce Odland,  &  composer Rinde Eckert join us to present some of the recordings, both secret and sanctioned, from The TANK Center for Sonic Arts, located in Rangley, Colorado.

episodesByNumber.title: #3982: With a Hint of Metal
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to a show where the Venn diagrams of new music and metal overlap. There's work from Kelly Moran, M. Lamar, David T. Little, Norway's Splashgirl, and New York composer Mick Barr.

episodesByNumber.title: #3983: Music From East and Southeast Africa
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music from parts of east and southeast Africa, including new music from Mokoomba of Zimbabwe, cross-cultural music from Kenya/Germany, and a tune from the band Monoswezi.

episodesByNumber.title: #3984: New Music for Trumpet - the Softer Side
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music for trumpet, modified trumpet and trumpet with electronics in new old music from Trio Mediaeval together with trumpeter Arve Henriksen, work by Yazz Ahmed,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3985: Music for an Imaginary American West
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music for an imaginary American west, including work from composer and multi-disciplinary artist Delia Gonzalez, the duo High Plains, and various film scores.

episodesByNumber.title: #3986: Electroacoustic Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music by composers from Iceland, Ireland, Germany  &  Sweden,  &  California who incorporate both electronic and acoustic sounds.

episodesByNumber.title: #3987: New Releases, May 2017
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear new music by Alex Somers for the Bill Morrison film 'Dawson City:Frozen Time', from Amir ElSaffar  &  Rivers of Sound, Kate Simko  &  the London Electronic Orchestra, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3988: Remembering David Lewiston
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music recorded by the late producer  &  ethnomusicologist David Lewiston of gamelan music from Indonesia, pan pipers from Peru,  &  chant of Tibetan monks.

episodesByNumber.title: #3989: Water-Based Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear water-based pieces from Philip Glass, pianist Omar Sosa, kora player Sona (Maya) Jobarteh  &  others for this edition of New Sounds.

episodesByNumber.title: #3990: Works for Voice and Drone
episodesByNumber.tease: Enjoy music for voice soaring over a drone in works by Hildegard of Bingen, Sir John Tavener, and ancient music of Scandinavia, as performed by members of Ensemble Mare Balticum.

episodesByNumber.title: #3991: Small Ensemble Works for Guitar(s) & Harp
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear works featuring two guitars, guitar and keyboards, or guitar and harp by the likes of Maeve Gilchrist with Viktor Krauss, guitarist Anthony Phillips (Genesis), and James Blackshaw.

episodesByNumber.title: #3992: Early Music Vocals & an Improvising Instrumentalist
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear a selection of works involving early music vocals  &  an improvising instrumentalist, including some of the latest record by Trio Mediaeval  &  Norwegian trumpeter Arve Henriksen.

episodesByNumber.title: #3993: New York Guitar Festival 2017 Highlights
episodesByNumber.tease: From the New Sounds Live concert series in The Greene Space, hear New York Guitar Festival 2017 highlights. There's music from Trixie Whitley, Dom Flemons, Marc Ribot, and Julian Lage.

episodesByNumber.title: #3994: With Saltland, aka Rebecca Foon & More Music from Montreal
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music from the Montreal-based cellist, climate activist and organizer Rebecca Foon, operating as her one-woman band, Saltland, live in the studio. Plus, more music from Montreal.

episodesByNumber.title: #3995: New Releases, June 2017
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music from sax quartet PRISM  &  So Percussion, music for sax  &  synth by Jonah Parzen-Johnson,  &  music that lands squarely between jazz  &  classical by guitarist Diego Barber,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3996: Coal
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear works inspired by coal with new music by Public Service Broadcasting, Julia Wolfe's Pulitzer Prize-winning "Anthracite Fields,"  &  Jóhann Jóhannsson's score The Miners' Hymns.

episodesByNumber.title: #3997: Piano Solos & Songs
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to piano music by producer/composer Chilly Gonzales with  &  without Jarvis Cocker, solo piano works and two-piano works by Meredith Monk, music by Christopher Cerrone, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #3998: Folk Songs
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to the Kronos Quartet's arrangements of traditional folk songs, featuring Rhiannon Giddens, Olivia Chaney, Sam Amidon, and Natalie Merchant. Plus, music by Kaia Kater  &  Hite.

episodesByNumber.title: #3999: Music In Counterpoint
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music by contemporary composers interested in counterpoint, like the Montreal-based Tim Hecker, the late Elodie Lauten, Steve Reich, Christian Biegai, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #4000: New Sounds Live, The First 30 Years
episodesByNumber.tease: For this show, listen to highlights from the first 30 years of New Sounds Live shows, ranging from throat-singing to big brass bands, a trombone shout choir and Brazilian bossa grooves.

episodesByNumber.title: #4001: Percussion Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to percussion music -thoughtful, considered, spatially-aware works- from metal, wood,  &  stones, featuring the Los Angeles Percussion Quartet, So Percussion, Olivier Alary  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #4002: Music For Accordions
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music for accordion,  &  members of the accordion family from Spain's Basque region by Kepa Junkera  &  Sorginak, from the Belgian Diab Quintet, to music of the late Pauline Oliveros.

episodesByNumber.title: #4003: Voices of Asia
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear voices from Asia, including Gong Linna (China), Yungchen Lhamo (Tibet), Sainkho (Tuva), and music from Afghan singer Simin Tander and Azerbaijani singers Alim and Fargana Qasimov.

episodesByNumber.title: #4004: A Recent Sampler of World Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Sample world music records for this New Sounds, featuring music from Kefaya, Iraqi-American trumpeter Amir ElSaffar,  &  music from the Ethiopian-born, Oakland-based artist Meklit.

episodesByNumber.title: #4005: Blurred Electronic/Acoustic Works
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear mostly electronic works that use acoustic sounds in a way that blurs the distinction between the two from the likes of Kaitlyn Aurelia Smith, Floating Points, Balmorhea, and Oregon.

episodesByNumber.title: #4006: Works for Instrument Multiples
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear works for instrument multiples, including music by Nils Frahm, Donnacha Dennehy for Nadia Sirota  &  Liam Byrne, Shannon Hayden, Garth Knox  &  Caoimhín Ó Raghallaigh,  &  Peter Gregson.

episodesByNumber.title: #4007: July 2017 New Releases
episodesByNumber.tease: New releases for this month include choral music with Native American flute, and recordings that pair Scandinavian  &  Western musicians with musicians from Northern  &  Southern Africa.

episodesByNumber.title: #4008: Music by Jazz-Adjacent Artists
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear jazz-adjacent music from the UK quartet Dinosaur, Laura Jurd's Mercury Prize-nominated band, the downtown-y garage-chamber jazz septet The Cellar and Point, Chet Doxas, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #4009: New Sounds of Old Folk Songs
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear new approaches to old folk songs from Trad.Attack!, Dálava, Sam Lee, in music from Estonia and Moravian folksongs, and arrangements of songs from the British travelers community.

episodesByNumber.title: #4010: Stringed Instruments and Electronics
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear works for stringed instruments and electronics, with music for several layers of cellist Zoe Keating, bassist/composer Florent Ghys, cello and electronics by High Plains, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #4011: Music Inspired by Ragas
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music inspired by Indian ragas from Kronos Quartet, Fifth House Ensemble, Arun Ramamurthy Trio, music by Kay Gardner from an archival LP, and a microtonal raga by John Cage.

episodesByNumber.title: #4012: Music Inspired by NASA
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music inspired by NASA and the space missions of the 1960s and '70s, featuring the bands Public Service Broadcasting and Quindar, jazz pianist Kit Downes, and Penguin Café.

episodesByNumber.title: #4013: Chamber Jazz
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear chamber jazz, both archival and brand new - with works from piano legend Ahmad Jamal, percussionist Tyshawn Sorey, and Finnish-born NY-based guitarist/composer Olli Hirvonen.

episodesByNumber.title: #4014: All in the Lute Family
episodesByNumber.tease: There's music for many members of the lute family, from pipa to mandolin, from ngoni to charango, and the best known of these instruments - the guitar - for this New Sounds.

episodesByNumber.title: #4015: Everything Revolves Around The Sun
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music that revolves around the sun, featuring music from Estonian band Trad.Attack!, the duo Rabbit Rabbit Radio, Warsaw Village Band, and A Winged Victory for the Sullen.
tags: a winged victory for the sullen

episodesByNumber.title: #4016: More Songs About the Sun
episodesByNumber.tease: For this episode, hear more songs about the sun, in the voices of The Crossing singing John Luther Adams, looped and textured music by Emily Wells, Jacaszek, and Jon Hopkins.

episodesByNumber.title: #4017: The Earliest Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to old sounds, including music from Ergodos Musicians playing Leonin, Gyða Valtysdóttir plays the world's oldest surviving musical composition,  &  music by Hildegard von Bingen.

episodesByNumber.title: #4018: New Releases, August 2017
episodesByNumber.tease: Sample new music that came our way from Chicago's Mucca Pazza, London's Portico Quartet, Danish experimental supergroup Girls In Airports, works by Molly Joyce and Leah Kardos,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #4019: Cross-Cultural Smorgasbord of World Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear cross-cultural music from Madagascar, Mali, and France, along with songs in Ladino from the Guy Mendilow Ensemble. Plus, hear music via Europe, Mongolia and Iran from Meikhâneh.

episodesByNumber.title: #4020: Electroacoustic Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear electroacoustic music from British-based Leah Kardos, Ireland's Donnacha Dennehy writing for the violist Nadia Sirota, new music from the Canadian chamber band Esmerine, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #4021: Electronic Music, Old and New
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music from the late bass player  &  co-founder of the band, CAN, Holger Czukay. Plus, hear music by synthesist Kaitlyn Aurelia Smith, and electronic music pioneer Laurie Spiegel.

episodesByNumber.title: #4022: Small Seeds, Big Pieces (Piano Edition)
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear big pieces that grow from little musical seeds by Russian composer and pianist Anton Batagov, American composer Marti Epstein, and music from Stephen Scott's Bowed Piano Ensemble.

episodesByNumber.title: #4023: Electric Guitar Soundscapes
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear cinematic guitar-based soundscapes from Noveller, Ancient Ocean, the Austin-based duo Balmorhea, along with a pedal-steel based guitarscape from Chas Smith and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #4024: At Sea - Nautically Themed Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to nautically-themed music, and music about being lost, plus music built on sea shanties for this New Sounds.

episodesByNumber.title: #4025: The Ever-Changing World of Electronic Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear some electronic music from Ben Frost, Qasim Naqvi, Valiska,  &  Moscow-based pianist/composer Dmitry Evgrafov. Plus, hear an exclusive in-studio performance by Kaitlyn Aurelia Smith.

episodesByNumber.title: #4026: Tour of Babel - a Cross-Cultural Musical Odyssey
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear songs in many different languages – but no intentional confusion. Hear new 2017 music from Malian singer Leila Gobi, along with music from This Is How We Fly, Monoswezi,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #4027: New Music for Film
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to film scores from the Kasai Allstars – one of the Congotronics bands, who scored and starred in an entire film, Clint Mansell's "Loving Vincent,"  &  Mica Levi's "Under the Skin."

episodesByNumber.title: #4028: With Abraham Brody
episodesByNumber.tease: Multi-instrumentalist  &  composer Abraham Brody performs some of his Lithuanian folklore-infused music on violin, piano,  &  looping station- solo  &  with his band Pletai, in our studio.

episodesByNumber.title: #4029: New Releases, September 2017
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear new music for September from the Abatwa musicians of Rwanda, the Danish String Quartet, New Morse Code, Colleen,  &  the trio of Yacine Boularès, Vincent Segal,  &  Nasheet Waits.

episodesByNumber.title: #4030: With Composer, Conductor, Writer Matthew Aucoin
episodesByNumber.tease: Composer  &  conductor Matthew Aucoin visits the studio to talk about his opera, 'Crossing' - an ode to Walt Whitman, based on his Civil War diaries and his poetry.

episodesByNumber.title: #4031: Traffic Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music that deals with traffic, with works titled after specific NYC roads, and more generally music about the machines that cause the traffic: cars, trucks, trams, and buses.

episodesByNumber.title: #4032: Deep Listening, Music by Pauline Oliveros
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to a sampling of music by the late composer, accordionist, sound experimenter, and all-around musical pioneer Pauline Oliveros.

episodesByNumber.title: #4033: Unusual Covers
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear unexpected covers of The Velvet Underground, Bon Iver, and Beyoncé, by an American cello band, a jazz pianist, and a near-eastern trumpeter. Plus Colin Stetson's "Sorrow."

episodesByNumber.title: #4034: Music Based on Non-Western Forms
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music based on classical music forms from other parts of the world: Andalusian orchestras of N. Africa, Indonesian gamelan, Imperial Japanese gagaku,  &  classical ragas of India.

episodesByNumber.title: #4035: Minimalism Meets Electronics
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music that combines minimalism  &  electronic music, as with the Dusseldorf-based Grandbrothers, new work from multi-instrumentalist Colleen,  &  percussive work by ensemble, et al.

episodesByNumber.title: #4036: Talking Opera With John Adams, on "Girls of The Golden West"
episodesByNumber.tease: John Adams is talkin' opera for this New Sounds. The composer reflects on his interaction with opera, from "Nixon in China" to his latest with Peter Sellars, "Girls of The Golden West."

episodesByNumber.title: #4037, With Bjarte Eike and Barokksolistene (The Alehouse Boys)
episodesByNumber.tease: Folk fiddling, pub songs,  &  baroque music are all connected in music by Norwegian violinist Bjarte Eike  &  Barokksolisten. They play music from "The Alehouse Sessions" in-studio.

episodesByNumber.title: #4038: Cross-Cultural Chamber Music
episodesByNumber.tease: For this New Sounds, listen to unexpected chamber music collaborations by the band Sandcatchers, Daniel Herskedal  &  ensemble, Saeid Shanbehzadeh, Simo Lagnawi,  &  Helge Lien Trio.

episodesByNumber.title: #4039: New Music For Old Scandinavian Fiddles
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear new music for old Scandinavian fiddles - the Swedish nyckelharpa  &  Norwegian hardinfele (Hardanger fiddle) –together with near eastern, north African, jazz  &  electronic music.

episodesByNumber.title: #4040: New Sounds Live 2017: Ben Neill's "Manitoga" from Brookfield Place
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to the NYC premiere of Ben Neill's "Manitoga" (2014), composed for mutantrumpet, an ensemble of 4 players playing artist Carol Szymanski's brass sculptures, and environment.

episodesByNumber.title: #4041: New Releases, October 2017
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear new music by Empyrean Atlas, Ensemble et al, Brass Menažeri, Emily Pinkerton  &  NOW Ensemble, the Anat Cohen Tentet, Swedish-Finnish trio Folk'Avant  &  guitarist Pino Forastiere.

episodesByNumber.title: #4042: From New Sounds Live, A Tribute to Pauline Oliveros
episodesByNumber.tease: From the New Sounds Live concerts at Brookfield Place, Darmstadt Ensemble performs works in tribute to the late composer, accordionist, sound experimenter,  &  pioneer Pauline Oliveros.

episodesByNumber.title: #4043: Ever More Electronic Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear classic electronic music from pioneering composer Morton Subnotnick, along with very recent music by Laurel Halo, Delia Derbyshire Appreciation Society,  &  new music from Coupler.

episodesByNumber.title: #4044: Non-Western Chamber Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear the trio of Yacine Boularès, Vincent Segal,  &  Nasheet Waits. Plus, chamber music by John Zorn's Masada Project, West African kora, the Indian slide guitar,  &  the Chinese erhu.

episodesByNumber.title: #4045: With Thomas Adès & His Latest Opera - Where the Party Never Ends
episodesByNumber.tease: British composer, pianist  &  conductor Thomas Adès joins us to talk of surrealist film, extreme soprano range, ondes Martenot,  &  his latest opera, "The Exterminating Angel".

episodesByNumber.title: #4046: Theme And Variations - Pretty Polly
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear arrangements of the murder ballad, "Pretty Polly," featuring Emily Pinkerton, Patrick Burke  &  NOW Ensemble Shirley Collins,  &  Bryce Dessner's arrangement for eighth blackbird.

episodesByNumber.title: #4047: Instruments of the Mediterranean
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music featuring instruments of the Mediterranean, with works by Rebetiki Istoria, Zied Zouari Trio, Benjamim Taubkin, Xylouris White, Victor Herrero,  &  the Chalkias Family.

episodesByNumber.title: #4048: Voices, Accompanied, and Not
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music with multiple voices - accompanied in works by Andrew McKenne Lee or Frances White,  &  not, as in music by Danish composer Bo Holten or Estonian composer Arvo Pärt.

episodesByNumber.title: #4049: A Musical Tour of Italy
episodesByNumber.tease: Take a musical tour of Italy, including music by Albanian cellist Redi Hasa  &  vocalist Maria Mazzotta, new tunes from Canzoniere Grecanico Salentino, the group Hobocombo  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #4050: Music for Thumb Piano
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music that features African thumb piano from Lulendo, Konono No. 1, Monoswezi, Francis Bebey, and Kronos Quartet.

episodesByNumber.title: #4051: New Music By Syrian Musicians & Composers
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear an hour of orchestral, electronic,  &  improvised music – all written  &  played by musicians from Syria, including works by Maya Youssef, Basel Rajoub, Waed Bouhassoun,  &  Kinan Azmeh.

episodesByNumber.title: #4052: Art Songs or Pop Songs?
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music that falls somewhere between classical music  &  indie rock, and/or songs on the border of pop music  &  art music, by Gabriel Kahane, Thor  &  Friends, The Staves  &  yMusic,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #4053: New Releases, November 2017
episodesByNumber.tease: Sample new music from string trio 3MA, Balkan band Kries, oud player Tristan Driessens' Soolmaan Quintet, Malian guitarist Boubacar Traoré, Portland, OR's Peter Broderick  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #4054: Music for Big Bands
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear Mike Oldfield's "Tubular Bells" arranged for a colliery brass band, music from Munich-based Monika Roscher Big Band,  &  Kraftwerk, as played by the John Hollenbeck Large Ensemble.

episodesByNumber.title: #4055: Recent Electronic Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to an hour of electronic music, with music by Icelandic composer Ben Frost, Chicago-based Coupler, British composer Poppy Ackroyd, Ancient Ocean, Austin's Balmorhea,  &  Úlfur.

episodesByNumber.title: #4056: New Sounds Live: Colin Stetson's "Sorrow," Gorecki Reworked
episodesByNumber.tease: From the New Sounds Live concerts at Brookfield Place, hear "Sorrow" - sax player/composer Colin Stetson's reworking of Polish composer Henryk Gorecki's "Symphony of Sorrowful Songs."

episodesByNumber.title: #4057: Spiritual Jazz
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear some of John Coltrane's deeply spiritual record "A Love Supreme," along with a work from Coltrane's wife, Alice, plus music from one of her disciples, and one of his.

episodesByNumber.title: #4058: Guitar & Guitar Chamber Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to works for guitar, solo  &  in a chamber ensemble, including a trio featuring guitarist Efren Lopez, Danish guitarist Mikkel Ploug, music by the Baird Sisters,  &  James Blackshaw.

episodesByNumber.title: #4059: Music Rooted in Buddhist Chants
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music rooted in Buddhist chant from Japan, Tibet,  &  Southeast Asia, featuring Him Sophy's work, "Bangsokol: A Requiem for Cambodia," the Gyuto Monks,  &  sampled shomyo chant.

episodesByNumber.title: #4060: Music for Zithers and Dulcimers
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to a program of music for zithers and dulcimers, from Maya Youssef's kanun to Laraaji's electric zither, along with Vietnamese zither by Tri Nguyen, and citera by Lajkó Félix.

episodesByNumber.title: #4061: Musical Tour of the Eastern Mediterranean
episodesByNumber.tease: Take a musical tour of the Eastern Mediterranean, from Southern Italy and music by Ludovico Einaudi  &  Alessandra Belloni to Crete, and then around the horn to Israel  &  Egypt.

episodesByNumber.title: #4062: Memorable Musical Moments of 2017
episodesByNumber.tease: To wrap up 2017, listen to recordings and live performances from our studio, consisting largely of music which may have flown under the radar this year, from opera to stretch music.

episodesByNumber.title: #4063: Folk Meets Contemporary Classical
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music that brings together traditional British and American folk songs with the sounds of classical instrumentation, in works by Offa Rex, The Staves and yMusic, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #4064: New Music From South Africa
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to new music from South Africa for this New Sounds program, with works by Ladysmith Black Mambazo, duo pianists Kathleen Tagg and Andre Petersen, and Kevin Volans.

episodesByNumber.title: #4065: With Carla Kihlstedt, on 'Black Inscription'
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear violinist and vocalist Carla Kihlstedt on the song cycle, "Black Inscription," a collaboration with drummer Matthias Bossi and multi-instrumentalist Jeremy Flower.

episodesByNumber.title: #4066: John Schaefer's Top Ten of 2017
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to electro-acoustic cello from Montreal, music by a Balkan-influenced renaissance quartet, film music by Kasai All-Stars, music from Penguin Café, and Baroque-tavern party music.

episodesByNumber.title: #4067: Re-told Tales
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to musical settings of older texts, refashioned somehow, as in Olagón, a re-telling of an ancient Irish epic, words spoken by Ophelia from Hamlet, and poetry by Emily Brontë.

episodesByNumber.title: #4068: Drummer/Percussionist Composers
episodesByNumber.tease: Drummer/Percussionist composers are up front for this show. Hear music by Susie Ibarra, Jaimeo Brown, balafon-based Kanazoé Orkestra, Thor Harris (Swans), and ensemble et al.

episodesByNumber.title: #4069: World Music: Arab, Persian, Indian Collaborations
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear world music tied to Arab, Persian, or Indian music for this show, featuring works by The Epichorus, Kamancello, Nordic Raga, Kayhan Kalhor, and Yo-Yo Ma  &  the Silk Road Ensemble.

episodesByNumber.title: #4070: Updated European Folk Traditions
episodesByNumber.tease: Take a tour of updated Euro-folk traditions from Italy, Ireland, Poland,  &  and France. Also, hear Nordic neo-pagan music by Wardruna, Croatian band Kries, and Estonian folk band Rüüt.

episodesByNumber.title: #4071: With Nils Frahm
episodesByNumber.tease: German composer, pianist, and producer Nils Frahm presents his latest record, "All Melody," which combines new classical and electronic music, and uses all kinds of timbres and textures.

episodesByNumber.title: #4072: New Music for Reeds
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to new music for reeds from composer Lea Bertucci, contrabass clarinetist John McCowen, sax maestro Ryan Muncy, and Michael Gordon's work for seven bassoons. Plus, Colin Stetson.

episodesByNumber.title: #4073: Arctic Voices
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear Arctic voices in music by Inuk singer Tanya Tagaq, the yoik tradition of the Sámi people from Norway's Vajas and Finland's SOLJU, and music by Alaska native, John Luther Adams.

episodesByNumber.title: #4074: New Releases, January 2018
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music from Atlanta-based vocalist  &  composer Hanna Benn, Argentinian composer/producer Kaleema, Berlin-based composer/guitarist/producer Martyn Heyne,  &  new works from the U.K.

episodesByNumber.title: #4075: Treated and Mistreated Pianos
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music for pianos, insides and out, some electronically treated and some physically mistreated, by Kelly Moran, Grandbrothers, Poppy Ackroyd, and Nightports with Matthew Bourne.

episodesByNumber.title: #4076: Unusual String Instruments
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music for unusual strings, from Paolo Angeli's prepared guitar to South American instruments like the cuatro, charango, or ronroco in music by Aukai and Gustavo Santaolalla.

episodesByNumber.title: #4077: Musical Works Based On Found Sound
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear an hour music based on found sounds and field recordings with works from the Bang on a Can All-Stars, sound artist Melanie Velarde, jazz pianist Henrique Eisenmann, and Anenon.

episodesByNumber.title: #4078: Works for Female Voices
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music for female voices by Iranian-born Sahba Aminikia for the San Francisco Girls Chorus along with music by Montreal-based composer Sarah Davachi, work by John Zorn, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #4079: Musical Meditations on Loss
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to musical meditations on loss, largely for strings, a bit of piano, and plenty of spoken voice in works from Laurie Anderson and Kronos Quartet, Caleb Burhans, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #4080: Music For Duos
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music for duos by Welsh harpist Catrin Finch and Senegalese kora master Seckou Keita, Finnish duo Tapani Rinne and Teho Majamäki, and work from Ursula K. Le Guin and Todd Barton.

episodesByNumber.title: #4081: Voices from Tibet in Western Musical Settings
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to voices from Tibet, featuring music by Yungchen Lhamo and Anton Batagov, Tibetan nun Chöying Drolma and Steve Tibbets, and classic work by Lama Gyurme and Jean-Philippe Rykiel.

episodesByNumber.title: #4082: Genre-Hopping Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music from the gray areas between musical genres with works by French harpist Laura Perrudin, cellist Erik Friedlander, drummer Bobby Previte, GoGo Penguin, and Jherek Bischoff.

episodesByNumber.title: #4083: New Music From Estonia
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music from Estonia, from vocalist/violinist/looper Maarja Nuut, the folk-jazz-chamber music of Verbarium, Flemish-Estonian folk by Estbel, plus music by Veljo Tormis, and Arvo Pärt.

episodesByNumber.title: #4084: New Sounds Live at Merkin Hall with Bang On A Can All-Stars PCF 2018
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to two world premieres - one by Puerto Rican-born composer  &  robotics/electronics manipulator, Angélica Negrón, and the other by composer/performer/professor George Lewis,  &  more.

episodesByNumber.title: #4085: New Releases, February 2018
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music from the French Ethiojazz band Arat Kilo, cross-cultural Iranian group Sibarg Ensemble, music from pianist/composers Alfredo Rodriguez and Tigran Hamasyan, and more.

episodesByNumber.title: #4086: With Pianist Tom Rogerson
episodesByNumber.tease: English-born composer, improvising keyboardist, and founder of the band 3TrappedTigers, Tom Rogerson, joins us in the studio to perform original creations for piano and electronics.

episodesByNumber.title: #4087: Music for Harp
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music for harp, for Celtic harp from Brittany by way of India and Kashmir, for electric harp by the Portuguese group, Powertrio,  &  a bardic epic from Joanna Newsom.

episodesByNumber.title: #4088: Composer/Vocalists Who Happen To Be Women
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music by vocalist/composers, with a work by Lisa Bielawa for the San Francisco Girls Chorus, pieces by Hanna Benn, Pavo Pavo, Afrika Mamas, Kaleema, Tanya Tagaq, Colleen and others.

episodesByNumber.title: #4089: With Sussan Deyhim and Richard Horowitz
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music from Sussan Deyhim and Richard Horowitz, a media opera called "The House is Black," based on works and life of literary icon Iranian contemporary poet Forough Farrokhzad.

episodesByNumber.title: #4090: Music for Piano and Strings
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear many combinations of piano and strings in works by Canadian-born composer Sarah Davachi, from British composer Poppy Ackroyd, Norwegian guitarist Stephan Meidell and others.

episodesByNumber.title: #4091: Jazz Meets Japan
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music that blends jazz and/or traditional music of Japan, from the likes of flutist Nicole Mitchell, drummer Jaimeo Brown's Transcendance, Brooklyn Rider and Kojiro Umezaki.

episodesByNumber.title: #4092: With Irish Composer and Producer Daniel Figgis
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music from Ireland for this New Sounds episode, featuring composer and producer Daniel Figgis, presenting works from a new compilation of electronic art music.

episodesByNumber.title: #4093: Celebrating Women's Voices, and Music
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear works that challenge what a female voice should sound like and sing about, including music by Pamela Z, Moira Smiley, Jenny Scheinman, and Alice Coltrane Turiyasangitananda.

episodesByNumber.title: #4094: Playing With Saxes
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear works that have two things in common: the sound of the saxophone (or multiple saxes), and a sense of play. Listen to music by Syrinx Effect, PRISM Quartet, and Pharoah Sanders.

episodesByNumber.title: #4095: With David Garland, 'Verdancy'
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music by songwriter and multi-instrumentalist David Garland, who presents music from his latest work - a 4-CD collection called "Verdancy."

episodesByNumber.title: #4096: Cross-Cultural Dreams
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear an hour of cross-cultural music, all inspired by dreams. Far from sleepy, these works imagine possible musics from Persia, the Philippines, and a hybrid Nordic Raga.

episodesByNumber.title: #4097: With Guitarst/Composer Gyan Riley: 'Sprig'
episodesByNumber.tease: Guitarist and composer Gyan Riley performs and presents music from his latest record "Sprig." Plus, hear kora music adapted for guitar by Derek Gripper, and works by guitarist Kaki King.

episodesByNumber.title: #4098: New Releases, March 2018
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear new releases from Chad Lawson and Jean-Michel Blais, cross-cultural music by Kabantu, music from a film score by Rachel Grimes, Berlin-based Mouse on Mars, and others.

episodesByNumber.title: #4099: Music with Low-End Instruments
episodesByNumber.tease: Listen to music featuring instruments from the low end, including the bassoon, the tuba, the trombone, and the bass clarinet from Oracle Hysterical, Sons of Kemet, and Isotope 217.

episodesByNumber.title: #4100: Music with Descriptive Titles
episodesByNumber.tease: Hear music with descriptive titles, Steve Reich's "Music for 18 Musicians," Angélica Negrón's "Music for Students," and a riff on "Music for 18" by cornetist and composer Ben LaMar Gay.

episodesByNumber.title: #4101: Musicians From Here Playing Music From There
